<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatakse maantee-, raudtee-, vee- ja lennuliikluses &uuml;histranspordi korraldamise alused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act provides the bases for the organisation of public transport in road, railway, waterway and air traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>Maanteeliiklusena k&auml;sitatakse bussi-, trammi-, trollibussi- ja taksoliiklust, raudteeliiklusena rongi- ja r&ouml;&ouml;basbussiliiklust, veeliiklusena laeva-, v&auml;ikelaeva- ja parvlaevaliiklust ning lennuliiklusena &otilde;hus&otilde;idukiliiklust. </eesti>
<inglise>Bus, tram, trolleybus and taxi traffic is deemed to be road traffic, train and railbus traffic is deemed to be railway traffic, ship, small craft and ferry traffic is deemed to be waterway traffic and aircraft traffic is deemed to be air traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevas seaduses ei k&auml;sitleta raudtee-, vee- ja lennuliikluses s&otilde;itjate veoks vajalike tegevuslubade ning k&otilde;igis veoliikides kiirabi- ja meditsiinitranspordi tegevuslubade v&auml;ljaandmise, pikendamise, peatamise ning kehtetuks tunnistamise korda ja tingimusi, mida reguleeritakse teiste seadustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) This Act does not provide the procedure and conditions for the grant, extension, suspension and revocation of licences for the carriage of passengers by railway, waterway and air traffic and of licences for ambulance transport by all modes of transport, which shall be regulated by other Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Motoriseerimata transpordivahendi kasutamist &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukina reguleeritakse kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksuse (edaspidi omavalitsus&uuml;ksus) &otilde;igusaktidega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The use of non-power driven transport vehicles for public transport vehicles shall be regulated by legislation issued by local governments (hereinafter local governments). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise>Definitions </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolevas seaduses on kasutatud j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise>The following definitions are used in this Act: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &uuml;histransport on tegevusloa alusel korraldatav tasuline s&otilde;itjatevedu (edaspidi &uuml;histransporditeenus). </eesti>
<inglise>1) "public transport" means the fee-charging carriage of passengers (hereinafter public transport services) organised on the basis of a licence. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;histransporditeenust osutatakse liiniveo, juhuveo v&otilde;i taksoveo korras; </eesti>
<inglise>Public transport services are provided by way of regular services, occasional services or taxi services; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vedaja on &uuml;histransporditeenuse osutamiseks tegevusluba omav &auml;riseadustikus (RT I 1995, 26-28, 355; 1998, 91-93, 1500; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 24, 360; 57, 596; 102, 907; 2000, 29, 172; 49, 303; 55, 365; 57, 373) nimetatud ja &auml;riregistrisse kantud ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i seaduse alusel teise registrisse kantud juriidiline isik; </eesti>
<inglise>2) "carrier" means an undertaking who holds a licence for the provision of public transport services, whose legal form is specified in the Commercial Code (RT I 1995, 26-28, 355; 1998, 91-93, 1500; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 24, 360; 57, 596; 102, 907; 2000, 29, 172; 49, 303; 55, 365; 57, 373) and who is entered in the commercial register, or a legal person entered in another register pursuant to law; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &uuml;hiss&otilde;iduk on &uuml;histransporditeenuse osutamiseks etten&auml;htud buss, s&otilde;iduauto, tramm, trollibuss, reisirong, r&ouml;&ouml;basbuss, reisilaev, reisiparvlaev, v&auml;ikelaev, &otilde;hus&otilde;iduk v&otilde;i muu mootori j&otilde;ul liikuv transpordivahend; </eesti>
<inglise>3) "public transport vehicle" means a bus, automobile, tram, trolleybus, passenger train, railbus, passenger ship, passenger ferry, small craft, aircraft or any other engine-driven means of transport prescribed for the provision of public transport services; </inglise>
<eesti>4) liinivedu on avaliku teenindamise lepingu alusel v&otilde;i kommertsliiniveona kindlal marsruudil ja s&otilde;iduplaani alusel korraldatav regulaarne s&otilde;itjatevedu, kus s&otilde;itjad saavad s&otilde;idukisse siseneda ja sealt v&auml;ljuda s&otilde;iduplaaniga m&auml;&auml;ratud peatustes; </eesti>
<inglise>4) "regular services" means the regular carriage of passengers on the basis of a public service contract or as commercial regular services provided on specified routes and on the basis of a timetable, where passengers may board and alight from a vehicle at stopping points determined in the timetable; </inglise>
<eesti>5) liinivedu avaliku teenindamise lepingu alusel (edaspidi avalik liinivedu) on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 10 ja 11 kohane vedaja ja omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse v&otilde;i riigi vahel s&otilde;lmitud avaliku teenindamise lepingu alusel korraldatav s&otilde;itjatevedu; </eesti>
<inglise>5) "regular services on the basis of a public service contract" (hereinafter public regular services) means the carriage of passengers organised on the basis of a public service contract entered into by a carrier and a local government or the state pursuant to &sect;&sect; 10 and 11 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kommertsliinivedu on liiniloa v&otilde;i tellijaga s&otilde;lmitud lepingu alusel korraldatav k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 32 l&otilde;igete 1 ja 3 kohane s&otilde;itjatevedu; </eesti>
<inglise>6) "commercial regular services" means the carriage of passengers organised on the basis of a line permit or contract entered into with an ordering party pursuant to subsections 32 (1) and (3) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>7) eriotstarbelise liiniveona k&auml;sitatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi punkti 4 n&otilde;udeid j&auml;rgides korraldatavaid j&auml;rgmisi vedusid: </eesti>
<inglise>7) the following transport operation organised in adherence with the requirements set out in clause 4) of this section is deemed to be" special regular services ": </inglise>
<eesti>- t&ouml;&ouml;liste vedu t&ouml;&ouml;le ja tagasi; </eesti>
<inglise>the carriage of workers to and from work; </inglise>
<eesti>- &otilde;pilaste ja &uuml;li&otilde;pilaste vedu &otilde;ppeasutusse ja tagasi; </eesti>
<inglise>the carriage of school pupils and students to and from educational institutions; </inglise>
<eesti>- s&otilde;jav&auml;elaste ja nende perekondade vedu ajutisse paiknemiskohta ja tagasi. </eesti>
<inglise>the carriage of military personnel and their families to and from a temporary area of stationing. </inglise>
<eesti>Eriotstarbelise liiniveo v&otilde;ib korraldada avaliku teenindamise lepingu alusel (eriotstarbeline avalik liinivedu) v&otilde;i kommertsalusel (eriotstarbeline kommertsliinivedu); </eesti>
<inglise>Special regular services may be organised on the basis of a public service contract (special public regular services) or on commercial basis (special commercial regular services). </inglise>
<eesti>8) kohalik liinivedu on s&otilde;itjate vedu maanteeliikluses valla-, linna- v&otilde;i maakonnaliinil, mille marsruut ning selle alg- ja l&otilde;pp-punkt asuvad sama valla, linna v&otilde;i maakonna haldusterritooriumil; </eesti>
<inglise>8) "local regular services" means the carriage of passengers by road traffic on rural municipality, urban or county lines the route and the starting and terminal points of which are located within the administrative territory of the same rural municipality, city or county; </inglise>
<eesti>9) kaugliinivedu on s&otilde;itjate vedu maanteeliikluses marsruudil, mille alg- ja l&otilde;pp-punkt asuvad eri maakondades; </eesti>
<inglise>9) "long-distance regular services" means the carriage of passengers by road traffic on routes the starting and terminal points of which are located in different counties; </inglise>
<eesti>10) juhuvedu on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 52 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud &uuml;ldeeskirjale vastav tellija v&otilde;i vedaja algatusel eelnevalt moodustatud s&otilde;itjater&uuml;hma vedu, mida ei k&auml;sitata liiniveona; </eesti>
<inglise>10) "occasional services" means the carriage of groups of passengers formed beforehand on the initiative of an ordering party or carrier in compliance with the general rules set out in subsection 52 (1) of this Act which are not deemed to be regular services; </inglise>
<eesti>11) taksovedu on s&otilde;itjate vedu tellija soovitud sihtkohta s&otilde;iduautoga (taksoga) v&otilde;i muu taksoveoks kohandatud &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukiga, v&auml;lja arvatud reisirong ja parvlaev; </eesti>
<inglise>11) "taxi service" means the carriage of passengers to a destination requested by the ordering party by means of an automobile (a taxi) or other public transport vehicle adjusted for the provision of taxi service, except by passenger trains and ferry; </inglise>
<eesti>12) bussivedu on s&otilde;itjate vedu bussiga. </eesti>
<inglise>12) "carriage by bus "means the carriage of passengers by bus. </inglise>
<eesti>Bussiveona v&otilde;ib k&auml;sitada ka s&otilde;itjate vedu 6-9 istekohaga (kaasa arvatud juhi koht) s&otilde;iduautoga; </eesti>
<inglise>The carriage of passengers by automobiles which have 6-9 seats (including the driver's seat) may also be considered as carriage by bus; </inglise>
<eesti>13) rahvusvaheline s&otilde;itjatevedu on s&otilde;itjate vedu riigipiiri &uuml;letaval marsruudil; </eesti>
<inglise>13) "international carriage of passengers" means the carriage of passengers on a route which crosses state borders; </inglise>
<eesti>14) &uuml;histranspordi infrastruktuuri objekt on &uuml;histransporditeenuse osutamiseks etten&auml;htud reisiterminal, bussi- v&otilde;i raudteejaam, sadam, kai, perroon, ootekoda, peatuskoht, informatsiooni- ja sides&uuml;steem ning muud liinirajatised ja seadmed ning nende teenindamiseks etten&auml;htud v&otilde;i vajalik inventar; </eesti>
<inglise>14) "objects of public transport infrastructure" means passenger terminals, bus and railway stations, ports, berths, platforms, shelters, stopping points, information and communication systems and other line constructions and equipment and inventory prescribed or needed for servicing thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>15) s&otilde;idukilomeetri tariif on &uuml;he kilomeetri s&otilde;iduhind; </eesti>
<inglise>15) "tariff per kilometre" means the cost of the journey per one kilometre; </inglise>
<eesti>16) s&otilde;idutunni tariif on &uuml;hiss&otilde;iduki kasutamise &uuml;he tunni hind; </eesti>
<inglise>16) "tariff per hour" means the cost of the use of a public transport vehicle for one hour; </inglise>
<eesti>17) s&otilde;idupilet on vormikohane dokument, mis t&otilde;endab s&otilde;itja &otilde;igust kasutada &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukit kindlal liinil v&otilde;i liiniv&otilde;rgus &uuml;heks v&otilde;i mitmeks s&otilde;iduks v&otilde;i kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>17) "transport ticket" means a standard format document which certifies the right of a passenger to use a public transport vehicle on a certain line or within a definite route network for one or several journeys or during designated time. </inglise>
