<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;histranspordi kavandamine ja korraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Planning and Organisation of Public Transport </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;histranspordi kavandamise ja korraldamise l&auml;htealused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for planning and organisation of public transport </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;leriigilist ning maakonna-, &uuml;ld- ja detailplaneeringut koostades tuleb arvestada &uuml;histranspordi ja selle liiniv&otilde;rgu arendamise vajadust, l&auml;htudes k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud eesm&auml;rkidest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the preparation of the national plan and of county, comprehensive and detailed plans, the need to develop public transport and its route network shall be taken into consideration on the basis of the objectives specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;histranspordi kavandamise ja korraldamise eesm&auml;rk on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The objectives for the planning and organisation of public transport are to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ressursside kasutamise sotsiaalset ja majanduslikku otstarbekust arvestades tagada &uuml;histransporditeenuse pakkumise vastavus n&otilde;udlusele, mis tuleneb elanike ja nende eri kategooriate (sealhulgas puuetega inimesed, vanurid, &otilde;pilased ja &uuml;li&otilde;pilased, saarte ja v&auml;ikesaarte elanikud) liikumisvajadusest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) ensure that the supply of public transport services meets the demand prompted by the need for movement of residents and different categories thereof (including disabled persons, the elderly, school pupils, students, residents of islands and small islands) taking into consideration the social and economic feasibility of the use of resources; </inglise>
<eesti>2) soodustada &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukite eeliskasutamist s&otilde;iduautode ja teiste individuaals&otilde;idukitega v&otilde;rreldes, v&auml;hendades sellega transpordi negatiivset m&otilde;ju keskkonnale ja sellest p&otilde;hjustatud tervisekahjustusi ning aidates kaasa liiklus&otilde;nnetuste ja liiklusummikute &auml;rahoidmisele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) promote the preferential use of public transport vehicles in comparison with automobiles and other means of individual transport and thereby, to reduce the negative effects of transport on the environment and the physical harm caused by transport and to facilitate the prevention of traffic accidents and congestion; </inglise>
<eesti>3) v&auml;hendada &uuml;hiskonna kulutusi transpordile ja energiale ning sotsiaalsele ja majanduslikule infrastruktuurile. </eesti>
<inglise>3) reduce the costs on transport, energy and social and economic infrastructure incurred by the society. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;histransporti kavandavad ja korraldavad asutused </eesti>
<inglise>Agencies which plan and organise public transport </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;histransporti kavandavad ja korraldavad k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel s&auml;testatud korras valla- ja linnavolikogu ning valla- ja linnavalitsus (edaspidi omavalitsusorgan), maavalitsus, Teede- ja Sideministeerium ning Vabariigi Valitsus, vajaduse korral kaasates omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liite ning vedajaid ja vedajate &uuml;hendusi. </eesti>
<inglise>Rural municipality and city councils, rural municipality and city governments (hereinafter local government bodies), county governments, the Ministry of Transport and Communications and the Government of the Republic shall plan and organise public transport pursuant to the procedure provided for in this Act or pursuant to the procedure established on the basis of this Act and, if necessary, involve local government associations, carriers and associations of carriers in the planning and organising. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsusorgani &uuml;lesanded </eesti>
<inglise>Functions of local government bodies </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Omavalitsusorgan oma haldusterritooriumil: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Within the administrative territory of a local government body, the local government body shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) suunab ja koordineerib &uuml;histranspordi arengut ning t&ouml;&ouml;tab v&auml;lja ja viib ellu asjaomaseid arengukavasid, mida rahastatakse omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse eelarvest, riigieelarvest ning ettev&otilde;tjate sihteraldistest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) direct and co-ordinate the development of public transport, elaborate and implement relevant development plans financed out of the budget of the local government, the state budget and appropriations made for specific purposes by undertakings; </inglise>
<eesti>2) korraldab elanike liikumisvajaduse uuringuid, et selgitada v&auml;lja n&otilde;udlus &uuml;histransporditeenuse j&auml;rele ning eri liiki vedude korraldamise otstarbekus ja v&otilde;imalused; m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks &uuml;histranspordi teenindustaseme normid valla- v&otilde;i linnaliinidel ning koos vedajatega tagab nende j&auml;rgimise; </eesti>
<inglise>2) organise surveys of the residents' need for movement to clarify the demand for public transport services and the feasibility and possibilities to organise different transport operations; shall determine the standards of the service level for public transport on rural municipality or urban lines and, together with the carriers, ensure compliance therewith; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kujundab valla v&otilde;i linna &uuml;histranspordi liiniv&otilde;rgu, mis on seotud maakonna ja &uuml;leriigilise v&otilde;rguga, ning kinnitab valla- v&otilde;i linnaliinide s&otilde;iduplaanid, arvestades maakonnaliinide ja kaugliinide s&otilde;iduplaane; </eesti>
<inglise>3) draft a public transport route network for the city or rural municipality which shall be related to county and national networks and approve the timetables for rural municipality or urban lines taking into consideration the timetables for county lines and long-distance lines; </inglise>
<eesti>(07.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.02.2001 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </inglise>
<eesti>4) korraldab &uuml;histranspordi infrastruktuuri objektide planeerimist, rajamist, korrashoidu ja kasutamist ning v&otilde;tab meetmeid &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukitele soodusliiklusolude loomiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) organise the planning, construction, maintenance and use of the objects of public transport infrastructure and take measures to create preferential traffic conditions for public transport vehicles; </inglise>
<eesti>5) annab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 34 etten&auml;htud juhtudel s&otilde;itjateveo tegevuslubasid ja liinilubasid; </eesti>
<inglise>5) grant licences for the carriage of passengers and line permits in the cases prescribed in &sect; 34 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>6) s&otilde;lmib vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 12 s&auml;testatule vedajatega avaliku teenindamise lepinguid ning korraldab avalikke konkursse vedajate valimiseks avalikule liiniveole ja kommertsliiniveole k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 34 l&otilde;ikes 5 loetletud juhtudel; </eesti>
<inglise>6) enter into public service contracts with carriers pursuant to the provisions of &sect; 12 of this Act and, in the cases listed in subsection 34 (5) of this Act, organise public competitions to select carriers to provide public or commercial regular services; </inglise>
<eesti>7) esitab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 20 alusel s&auml;testatud korras oma asukoha j&auml;rgsele maavalitsusele taotluse riigieelarvest valla v&otilde;i linna &uuml;histranspordi selle osa rahastamiseks, millel puudub kate omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse eelarves; </eesti>
<inglise>7) pursuant to the procedure provided on the basis of &sect; 20 of this Act, submit applications to the county government of its location for financing the public transport of the city or rural municipality from the state budget in the part not covered by the local government budget; </inglise>
<eesti>8) avaliku teenindamise lepingu alusel rahastab avalikku liinivedu oma eelarvest ja riigieelarvest ning ettev&otilde;tjate sihteraldistest; </eesti>
<inglise>8) on the basis of public service contracts, finance public regular services out of its budget, the state budget or single-purpose allocation of undertakings; </inglise>
<eesti>9) kehtestab valla- v&otilde;i linnaliinide avaliku liiniveo s&otilde;idukilomeetri tariifid v&otilde;i s&otilde;idupiletihinnad; </eesti>
<inglise>9) establish tariffs per kilometre and transport ticket prices for public regular services on rural municipality or urban lines; </inglise>
<eesti>10) h&uuml;vitab tema poolt kehtestatud s&otilde;idusoodustused; </eesti>
<inglise>10) compensate for travel fare concessions established by the local government body; </inglise>
<eesti>11) tagab koos vedajatega s&otilde;idupiletite m&uuml;&uuml;gikorralduse ja korraldab piletikontrolli valla- v&otilde;i linnaliinidel; </eesti>
<inglise>11) together with carriers, ensure organisation of the sale of transport tickets and organise ticket inspection on rural municipality or urban lines; </inglise>
<eesti>12) korraldab j&auml;relevalvet tema antud s&otilde;itjateveo tegevusloa ja liiniloa n&otilde;uete ning tema s&otilde;lmitud avaliku teenindamise lepingute t&auml;itmise &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>12) organise supervision of compliance with the requirements of licences for the carriage of passengers and line permits granted by the county government and performance of public service contracts entered into by the county government. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-4, 8, 11 ja 12 loetletud &uuml;lesandeid t&auml;idab omavalitsusorgan vajaduse korral koost&ouml;&ouml;s tema haldusterritooriumiga piirnevatel haldusterritooriumidel asuvate omavalitsusorganitega, asukohaj&auml;rgse maavalitsusega ja omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liiduga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If necessary, a local government body shall perform the functions listed in clauses (1) 1) -4), 8), 11) and 12) of this section in co-operation with the local government bodies whose administrative territories border on the administrative territory of the local government body, the county government of its location and the local government association. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Piirnevate haldusterritooriumidega omavalitsusorganid v&otilde;ivad omavahelisel ja asukohaj&auml;rgse maavalitsusega kokkuleppel toetada nende haldusterritooriume &uuml;hendavaid maakonnaliine oma eelarvest ja riigieelarve sihtotstarbelisest toetusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) By mutual agreement and by agreement with the county government of the location of local government bodies which have bordering administrative territories, such local government bodies may support the county lines which connect their administrative territories out of their budgets and subsidies allocated for such purposes from the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis loetletud omavalitsusorgani &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itja ja t&auml;itmise korra, kui need ei ole s&auml;testatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse teistes paragrahvides, m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu v&otilde;i tema volitusel valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A rural municipality or city council, or a rural municipality or city government upon authorisation of the rural municipality or city council shall assign an agency to perform the functions of a local government body listed in this section and shall determine the procedure for performance of the functions unless such functions are provided for in other sections of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Maavalitsuse &uuml;lesanded </eesti>
<inglise>Functions of county governments </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maavalitsus: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A county government shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) suunab ja koordineerib maakonna &uuml;histranspordi arengut ning t&ouml;&ouml;tab v&auml;lja ja viib ellu asjaomaseid arengukavasid, mida rahastatakse riigieelarvest, omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste eelarvetest ning ettev&otilde;tjate sihteraldistest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) direct and co-ordinate the development of public transport in the county, elaborate and implement relevant development plans financed out of the budgets of local governments, the state budget and single-purpose allocation of undertakings; </inglise>
<eesti>2) korraldab maakonna elanike liikumisvajaduse uuringuid, et selgitada v&auml;lja n&otilde;udlus &uuml;histransporditeenuse j&auml;rele ning eri liiki vedude korraldamise otstarbekus ja v&otilde;imalused; m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks &uuml;histranspordi teenindustaseme normid maakonnaliinidel ning koos vedajatega tagab nende j&auml;rgimise; </eesti>
<inglise>2) organise surveys of the residents' need for movement to clarify the demand for public transport services and the feasibility and possibilities to organise different transport operations; shall determine the standards of the service level for public transport on county lines and, together with the carriers, ensure compliance therewith; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kujundab maakonnas &uuml;leriigilise v&otilde;rguga seotud &uuml;histranspordi liiniv&otilde;rgu ja kinnitab maakonnaliinide s&otilde;iduplaanid, arvestades kaugliinide ning valla- ja linnaliinide s&otilde;iduplaane; </eesti>
<inglise>3) draft a public transport route network for the county which shall be related to the national network and approve the timetables for county lines taking into consideration the timetables for long-distance lines and county and urban lines; </inglise>
<eesti>(07.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.02.2001 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </inglise>
<eesti>4) korraldab maakonnaliinide infrastruktuuri objektide planeerimist, rajamist, korrashoidu ja kasutamist ning v&otilde;tab meetmeid &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukitele soodusliiklusolude loomiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) organise the planning, construction, maintenance and use of the objects of public transport infrastructure and take measures to create preferential traffic conditions for public transport vehicles; </inglise>
<eesti>5) annab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 34 etten&auml;htud juhtudel s&otilde;itjateveo tegevuslubasid ja liinilubasid; </eesti>
<inglise>5) grant licences for the carriage of passengers and line permits in the cases prescribed in &sect; 34 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>6) s&otilde;lmib vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 12 s&auml;testatule vedajatega avaliku teenindamise lepinguid ning korraldab avalikke konkursse vedajate valimiseks avalikule liiniveole ja kommertsliiniveole k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 34 l&otilde;ikes 5 loetletud juhtudel; </eesti>
<inglise>6) enter into public service contracts with carriers pursuant to the provisions of &sect; 12 of this Act and, in the cases listed in subsection 34 (5) of this Act, organise public competitions to select carriers to provide public or commercial regular services; </inglise>
<eesti>7) taotleb k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 20 alusel s&auml;testatud korras riigieelarvest toetust valla, linna ja maakonna &uuml;histranspordi rahastamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>7) pursuant to the procedure provided on the basis of &sect; 20 of this Act, apply for the financing of public transport in cities, rural municipalities or the county from the state budget; </inglise>
<eesti>8) avaliku teenindamise lepingu alusel rahastab avalikku liinivedu riigieelarvest, valla- ja linnavolikogude otsuste alusel nende eelarvetest ning ettev&otilde;tjate sihteraldistest; </eesti>
<inglise>8) on the basis of public service contracts, finance public regular services out of the state budget and, on the basis of resolutions by rural municipality or city councils, from the budgets of the rural municipalities and cities or from single-purpose allocations of undertakings; </inglise>
<eesti>9) t&ouml;&ouml;tab v&auml;lja ettepanekud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 24 l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 3 nimetatud avaliku liiniveo s&otilde;idukilomeetri tariifi v&otilde;i s&otilde;idupiletihinna kehtestamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>9) elaborate proposals for establishment of tariffs per kilometre and transport ticket prices for the public regular services specified in clause 24 (2) 3) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>10) tagab koos vedajatega s&otilde;idupiletite m&uuml;&uuml;gikorralduse ja korraldab piletikontrolli maakonnaliinidel; </eesti>
<inglise>10) together with carriers, ensure the organisation of the sale of transport tickets and organises ticket inspection on county lines; </inglise>
<eesti>11) korraldab j&auml;relevalvet tema antud s&otilde;itjateveo tegevusloa ja liiniloa n&otilde;uete ning tema s&otilde;lmitud avaliku teenindamise lepingute t&auml;itmise &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>11) organise supervision of compliance with the requirements of licences for the carriage of passengers and line permits granted by the county government and performance of public service contracts entered into by the county government. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-4 ja 7-11 loetletud &uuml;lesandeid t&auml;idab maavalitsus koost&ouml;&ouml;s maakonnas asuvate omavalitsus&uuml;ksustega ja omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liiduga ning maakonnaga piirnevate maakondade maavalitsustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A county government shall perform the functions listed in clauses (1) 1) -4) and 7) -11) of this section in co-operation with the local governments located in the county, local government association and the county governments of bordering counties. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Omavahelisel kokkuleppel v&otilde;ivad piirnevate maakondade maavalitsused toetada nende maakondi &uuml;hendavaid kaugliine riigieelarve ja omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste sihtotstarbelistest toetustest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) County governments of bordering counties may support, by mutual agreement, the county lines which connect their counties out of the subsidies allocated for such purposes from the state budget and the budgets of local governments. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Maavalitsus v&otilde;ib teha maakonna valla- ja linnavolikogudele ning omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liidule ettepaneku tsentraliseerida osa omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste eelarverahast, et kasutada seda maakonna &uuml;histranspordi arengukava rahastamiseks, maakonnaliinide toetamiseks ning s&otilde;idusoodustuste h&uuml;vitamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A county government may make a proposal to a rural municipality or city council or the local government association of the county for the centralisation of a part of the budgetary funds of a local government and for the use of the funds in order to finance the county's development plan for public transport, to support the county lines or to compensate for travel fare concessions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Piirkondlik &uuml;histranspordikeskus </eesti>
<inglise>Regional public transport centre </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Piirkondlik &uuml;histranspordikeskus on omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste ja riigi asutatud &auml;ri&uuml;hing v&otilde;i mittetulundus&uuml;hing, kus riigil ja omavalitsus&uuml;ksustel on enamusotsustus&otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Regional public transport centre is a company or non-profit association founded by a local government and the state where the state and the local government have majority interest. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) S&otilde;itjatevoogude piirkondlikest ise&auml;rasustest ning &uuml;histranspordi otstarbekama korraldamise vajadusest tulenevalt v&otilde;ivad omavalitsus&uuml;ksused ja riik volitada piirkondlikku &uuml;histranspordikeskust t&auml;itma neile k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 5 ja 6 pandud &uuml;lesandeid ning anda keskusele nende &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks vajaliku raha ja ainelised vahendid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Arising from the regional peculiarities of passenger flows and the need for effective organisation of public transport, local governments and the state may authorise a regional public transport centre to perform the functions imposed on them on the basis of &sect;&sect; 5 and 6 of this Act and to provide the centre with funds and material resources necessary for the performance of such functions. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Piirkondliku &uuml;histranspordikeskuse &uuml;lesanne on tagada elanikele keskuse asutajate etten&auml;htud tegevuspiirkonnas, selle territooriumi haldusjaotusest s&otilde;ltumata, soodsamad ja majanduslikult t&otilde;husamad &uuml;histransporditeenused, mille aluseks on &uuml;htne liiniv&otilde;rk, koosk&otilde;lastatud s&otilde;iduplaanid ning &uuml;htne piletis&uuml;steem. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The function of a regional public transport centre is to ensure that the residents of the territory prescribed by the founders of the centre, regardless of the administrative division of such territory, are provided with favourable and economic public transport services which shall be based on an integrated route network, co-ordinated timetables and an integrated ticket system. </inglise>
<eesti>Piirkondlik &uuml;histranspordikeskus ei v&otilde;i t&auml;ita vedaja funktsioone. </eesti>
<inglise>A regional public transport centre shall not perform the functions of a carrier. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Teede- ja Sideministeeriumi &uuml;lesanded </eesti>
<inglise>Functions of Ministry of Transport and Communications </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teede- ja Sideministeerium: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Ministry of Transport and Communications shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;tab v&auml;lja ja viib ellu &uuml;histranspordi pikaajalist riiklikku arengukava ja selle alaprogramme; </eesti>
<inglise>1) elaborate and implement a long-term national public transport development plan and the subprograms thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) korraldab &uuml;leriigilisi &uuml;histranspordiuuringuid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) conduct domestic public transport surveys; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kujundab rahvusvahelise liiniv&otilde;rguga seotud &uuml;leriigilise &uuml;histranspordi liiniv&otilde;rgu, kinnitab kaugliinide s&otilde;iduplaanid, arvestades maakonnaliinide s&otilde;iduplaane, ja koosk&otilde;lastab rahvusvaheliste liinide s&otilde;iduplaanid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) draft a domestic public transport route network which shall be connected to the international route network, approve the timetables for long-distance lines taking into consideration the timetables for county lines and co-ordinate the timetables of international lines; </inglise>
<eesti>(07.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.02.2001 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;tab v&auml;lja &uuml;histransporti korraldavatele riigi- ja omavalitsusasutustele ning vedajatele kohustusliku &uuml;histranspordi t&ouml;&ouml;- ja teenuste mahu arvutamise metoodika, teenindustaseme normid avalikule maakondadevahelisele liiniveole ja soovituslikud normid avalikule kohalikule liiniveole; </eesti>
<inglise>4) elaborate a mandatory methodology for calculation of work and service volumes in public transport to be used by state and local government agencies and carriers, standards for service level in inter-county public regular services and recommended standards for local public regular services; </inglise>
<eesti>5) t&ouml;&ouml;tab v&auml;lja ettepanekud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 24 l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 1 ja 2 nimetatud avaliku liiniveo s&otilde;idukilomeetri tariifi v&otilde;i s&otilde;idupiletihinna kehtestamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>5) elaborate proposals for establishment of tariffs per kilometre and transport ticket prices for the public regular services specified in clauses 24 (2) 1) and 2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 4 nimetatud teenindustaseme normid ning t&ouml;&ouml;- ja teenuste mahu arvutamise metoodika kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall establish the standards for service level and methodology for calculation of work and service volumes specified in clause (1) 4) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;itjateveo avaliku teenindamise leping </eesti>
<inglise>Public Service Contract for Carriage of Passengers </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Avaliku teenindamise kohustuse m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of public service obligation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avaliku teenindamise kohustus on vedaja v&otilde;etud kohustus korraldada oma &auml;rihuvist l&auml;htuva rahalise tasu eest avalikku liinivedu riigi v&otilde;i omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse tellitud mahus ja tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The "public service obligation" means an obligation assumed by a carrier to organise public regular services for remuneration based on the carriers' commercial interests in such volume and under such conditions as requested by the state or a local government. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avaliku teenindamise kohustus h&otilde;lmab tegutsemist, vedamist ja tariifide j&auml;rgimist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The public service obligation includes operation, carriage and the application of tariffs. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegutsemine t&auml;hendab vedaja kohustust tegevusloa alusel osutada kvaliteetset j&auml;rjepidevat &uuml;histransporditeenust ja vajaduse korral lisateenust ning kohustust p&auml;rast teenuste osutamise l&otilde;petamist tagastada t&ouml;&ouml;korras olekus temale lepingu alusel kasutada antud &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukid ja liinirajatised. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) "Operation" means an obligation imposed upon carriers to provide high-quality and continuous public transport services and, if necessary, additional services, and an obligation to return in working order, after public transport services have been withdrawn, the public transport vehicles and line facilities routes which were transferred to the carrier on a contractual basis. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Vedamine t&auml;hendab vedaja kohustust vedada s&otilde;itjaid veolepingus etten&auml;htud tingimustel ja tariifiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) "Carriage" means an obligation imposed upon carriers to carry passengers under the terms and conditions and for tariffs prescribed by a contract of carriage. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tariifide j&auml;rgimine t&auml;hendab vedaja kohustust rakendada teatava kategooria s&otilde;itjate v&otilde;i teatava kategooria kaupade veol ning teatavatel liinidel riigi v&otilde;i omavalitsusorgani kehtestatud v&otilde;i koosk&otilde;lastatud veotariife, mida ta oma &auml;rihuvi arvestades rakendab &uuml;ksnes tellija makstava h&uuml;vitise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) "Application of tariffs" means an obligation imposed upon carriers to apply, for certain categories of passengers or goods or on certain lines, carriage tariffs established or approved by the state or a local government body which the carrier, considering its own commercial interests, applies only if respective compensation is received from the ordering party. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Avaliku teenindamise leping </eesti>
<inglise>Public service contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avaliku teenindamise kohustuse saab vedajale panna &uuml;ksnes avaliku teenindamise lepingu alusel, mille s&otilde;lmivad veo tellija, keda esindab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 12 nimetatud p&auml;dev ametiasutus, ja avaliku konkursi alusel valitud vedaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The public service obligation may be imposed on a carrier only on the basis of a public service contract entered into between the party ordering the transport operation, represented by a competent agency specified in &sect; 12 of this Act, and a carrier selected on the basis of a public competition. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigihangete seaduse (RT I 1995, 54, 883; 1997, 9, 79; 1998, 38, 561; 1999, 16, 271; 92, 824; 97, 859; 2000, 57, 374; 84, 534; 2001, 7, 17) &sect;-s 4 nimetatud maksumuse &uuml;letamise korral korraldatakse avatud pakkumisega riigihankekonkurss riigihangete seaduses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>If the cost specified in &sect; 4 of the Pubic Procurement Act (RT I 1995, 54, 883; 1997, 9, 79; 1998, 38, 561; 1999, 16, 271; 92, 824; 97, 859; 2000, 57, 374; 84, 534; 2001, 7, 17) is exceeded, a public procurement with open tendering procedure shall be organised pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Public Procurement Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avaliku teenindamise kohustuse v&otilde;ib panna konkurentsiseaduse (RT I 1998, 30, 410; 1999, 89, 813; 2000, 53, 343; RT III 2000, 21, 232) &sect; 17 kohaselt ka eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igusega vedajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The public service obligation may be imposed on a carrier who has special rights or the exclusive right pursuant to &sect; 17 of the Competition Act (RT I 1998, 30, 410; 1999, 89, 813; 2000, 53, 343; RT III 2000, 21, 232). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avaliku teenindamise lepinguga m&auml;&auml;ratakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A public service contract shall determine: </inglise>
<eesti>1) avaliku teenindamise kohustus, mis h&otilde;lmab teenindatavate liinide loetelu, ja selle t&auml;itmise eest vedajale makstav raha; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the public service obligation which includes the list of lines to be serviced and remuneration paid to the carrier for compliance with the obligation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) veoteenuse osutamiseks &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukite ja liinirajatiste andmine ning nende kasutamise ja tagastamise n&otilde;uded; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the provision of public transport vehicles and line facilities for the provision of transport services and requirements concerning the use and return thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>3) lepingu l&otilde;ppemise v&otilde;i l&otilde;petamise ja muutmise korda k&auml;sitlevad s&auml;tted; </eesti>
<inglise>3) provisions concerning the procedures for the expiry, termination and amendment of the contract; </inglise>
<eesti>4) lepingu kehtimise aeg; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the period of validity of the contract; </inglise>
<eesti>5) s&otilde;itjate ja vara kindlustamise tingimused; </eesti>
<inglise>5) conditions for insuring passengers and property; </inglise>
<eesti>6) sanktsioonid; </eesti>
<inglise>6) penalties; </inglise>
<eesti>7) muud tingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>7) other terms and conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Avaliku teenindamise lepingu alusel transporditeenuste osutamisega seotud vara v&otilde;ib kuuluda vedajale v&otilde;i olla lepinguga antud tema valdusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The property related to the provision of transport services on the basis of a public service contract may belong to the carrier or be transferred to the carrier's possession on the basis of the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Avaliku teenindamise esmakordne leping s&otilde;lmitakse vedajaga v&auml;hemalt kaheks aastaks ning iga j&auml;rgmine leping v&auml;hemalt viieks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The first public service contract between an ordering party and a carrier shall be entered into for at least two years and each subsequent contract for at least five years. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 11 punkti 4 kohaseks lennu&uuml;henduseks s&otilde;lmitakse esmakordne avaliku teenindamise leping v&auml;hemalt &uuml;heks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>The first public service contract for the provision of an air connection pursuant to the provisions of clause 12 (1) 4) of this Act between an ordering party and a carrier shall be entered into for at least one year. </inglise>
<eesti>Vedaja soovil s&otilde;lmitakse temaga avaliku teenindamise leping ka eelnimetatud t&auml;htaegadest l&uuml;hemaks ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>A public service contract between an ordering party and a carrier may also be entered into for a shorter period than the terms specified above if the carrier so desires. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Avaliku teenindamise lepingus (kaasa arvatud eriotstarbelise liiniveo leping) tuleb s&auml;testada, et tegevusloa t&auml;htaja l&otilde;ppemise v&otilde;i loa kehtetuks tunnistamise korral leping l&otilde;peb. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A public service contract (including a contract for special regular services) shall provide that the contract expires upon the expiry or revocation of the licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kui tegevusloa t&auml;htaeg l&otilde;peb avaliku teenindamise lepingu t&auml;htajast varem, peab vedaja enne tegevusloa t&auml;htaja l&otilde;ppemist esitama tegevusluba andvale asutusele taotluse uue tegevusloa saamiseks seadusega etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) If a licence expires earlier than the public service contract, the carrier shall, before expiry of the licence, submit an application for the grant of a new licence pursuant to the procedure provided by law to the agency which granted the licence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Avaliku teenindamise lepingu alusel korraldatavad veod </eesti>
<inglise>Transport operation organised on basis of public services contract </inglise>
<eesti>Avaliku teenindamise lepingu alusel v&otilde;ib s&otilde;itjaid vedada j&auml;rgmistel liinidel: </eesti>
<inglise>Passengers may be carried on the following lines on the basis of a public service contract: </inglise>
<eesti>1) raudteel, v&auml;lja arvatud rahvusvahelised rongiliinid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) railway lines, except international trains; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kohalikel bussiliinidel ning trammi- ja trollibussiliinidel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) local bus lines and tram and trolleybus lines; </inglise>
<eesti>3) Eesti mandri ja saarte ning v&auml;ikesaarte vahelistel, Saaremaa ja Hiiumaa vahelisel ning Saaremaa ja Saare maakonna haldusterritooriumil asuvate v&auml;ikesaarte vahelistel laeva-, v&auml;ikelaeva- ja parvlaevaliinidel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) ship, small ship and ferry lines which connect the Estonian mainland with the islands and small islands, the island of Saaremaa with the island of Hiiumaa and the island of Saaremaa with the small islands located within the administrative territory of Saare county; </inglise>
<eesti>4) Eesti mandri ja saarte ning v&auml;ikesaarte vahelistel, Saaremaa ja Hiiumaa vahelisel ning Saaremaa ja Saare maakonna haldusterritooriumil asuvate v&auml;ikesaarte vahelistel lennuliinidel. </eesti>
<inglise>4) air lines which connect the Estonian mainland with the islands and small islands, the island of Saaremaa with the island of Hiiumaa and the island of Saaremaa with the small islands located within the administrative territory of Saare county. </inglise>
<eesti>5) piirnevaid maakondi &uuml;hendavatel kaugliinidel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 6 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud juhul; </eesti>
<inglise>5) long-distance lines connecting bordering counties in the case specified in subsection 6 (3) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>(07.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.02.2001 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;dev ametiasutus </eesti>
<inglise>Competent agency </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 10 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud p&auml;dev ametiasutus on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The competent agencies specified in subsection 10 (1) of this Act are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Teede- ja Sideministeerium v&otilde;i teede- ja sideministri volitatud ametiasutus raudteeliikluses korraldataval s&otilde;itjateveol (v&auml;lja arvatud linnasisene vedu); </eesti>
<inglise>1) the Ministry of Transport and Communications or an agency authorised by the Minister of Transport and Communications in the carriage of passengers organised in railway traffic (except in the urban carriage of passengers); </inglise>
<eesti>2) Teede- ja Sideministeerium v&otilde;i teede- ja sideministri volitatud ametiasutus laeva-, v&auml;ikelaeva- ja parvlaeva- ning lennuliikluses korraldataval maakondadevahelisel ja &uuml;leriigilisel s&otilde;itjateveol; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the Ministry of Transport and Communications or an agency authorised by the Minister of Transport and Communications in the inter-county and national carriage of passengers in ship, small ship or ferry traffic or aircraft traffic; </inglise>
<eesti>3) maavalitsus bussi-, laeva-, v&auml;ikelaeva- ja parvlaeva- ning lennuliikluses maakonnasisesel s&otilde;itjateveol, samuti kaugliiniveol k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 6 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud juhul; </eesti>
<inglise>3) county governments in the carriage of passengers within the county in bus, ship, small ship, ferry or aircraft traffic and upon long-distance regular services in the case specified in subsection 6 (3) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>(07.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.02.2001 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </inglise>
<eesti>4) valla- ja linnavalitsus v&otilde;i nende volitatud ametiasutus bussi-, trammi-, trollibussi- ning laeva-, v&auml;ikelaeva- ja parvlaevaliikluses valla- v&otilde;i linnasisesel s&otilde;itjateveol; </eesti>
<inglise>4) rural municipality and city governments or an agency authorised by these in the carriage of passengers in bus, tram, trolleybus or ship, small ship or ferry traffic within the rural municipality or city; </inglise>
<eesti>5) linnavalitsus v&otilde;i tema volitatud ametiasutus raudteeliikluses korraldataval linnasisesel s&otilde;itjateveol. </eesti>
<inglise>5) city governments or agencies authorised by a city government in the urban carriage of passengers in railway traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;dev ametiasutus v&otilde;ib olla ka k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 alusel asutatav piirkondlik &uuml;histranspordikeskus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The regional public transport centre founded pursuant to &sect; 7 of this Act may also be an authorised agency. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 3 nimetatud kaugliiniveo korral s&otilde;lmib vedajaga avaliku teenindamise lepingu see maavalitsus, kelle maakonna territooriumil kulgeb k&otilde;ige pikem osa piirnevaid maakondi &uuml;hendavast kaugliinist v&otilde;i kes nende maakondade maavalitsuste omavahelisel kokkuleppel on selleks volitatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the case of long-distance regular services specified in clause (1) 3) of this section, a public service contract with the carrier shall be entered into by the county government on whose county territory the longest part of a long-distance line connecting bordering counties is located or which is authorised to do so by agreement of the county governments of such counties. </inglise>
<eesti>(07.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.02.2001 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Avaliku liiniveo majandusarvestuse eraldamine muust ettev&otilde;tlusest </eesti>
<inglise>Separation of accounting of public regular services from other business activities </inglise>
<eesti>Kui vedaja korraldab peale avaliku liiniveo ka kommertsliinivedu v&otilde;i tegeleb muu ettev&otilde;tlusega, tuleb avaliku liiniveo majandusarvestus muu ettev&otilde;tlustegevuse arvestusest eraldada, arvestades j&auml;rgmisi n&otilde;udeid: </eesti>
<inglise>If in addition to public regular services, a carrier also organises commercial regular services or engages in other business activities, the accounting of the public regular services shall be separate from the accounting of other business activities considering the following requirements: </inglise>
<eesti>1) avaliku teenindamise lepingu kohase tegevuse kohta on vaja sisse seada raamatupidamine ning selle tegevusega seotud varaosa tuleb arvestada heast raamatupidamistavast l&auml;htuvalt; </eesti>
<inglise>1) accounting shall be maintained concerning activities included in the public service contract and the part of the property related to such activities shall be valued pursuant to good accounting practices; </inglise>
<eesti>2) avaliku liiniveo kulud peavad olema kaetud piletitulu ning riigieelarvest v&otilde;i omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse eelarvest antava toetusega, raha &uuml;lekandmine teistesse valdkondadesse v&otilde;i teistest valdkondadest on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>2) costs related to public regular services shall be covered by the revenue from the sale of tickets and subsidies granted from the state or local government budget; it is prohibited to transfer funds to or from other areas. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;histranspordi toetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Subsidies to Public Transport </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigi ja omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse toetus </eesti>
<inglise>Subsidies by state and local government </inglise>
<eesti>Riik ja omavalitsus&uuml;ksus annavad oma eelarvest sihtotstarbelist toetust avaliku liiniveo korraldamiseks, &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukite soetamiseks, &uuml;histranspordi infrastruktuuri objektide rajamiseks v&otilde;i uuendamiseks ja &uuml;histranspordiuuringute korraldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>The state and local governments shall grant subsidies intended for specific purposes from their budgets for the provision of public regular services, acquisition of public transport vehicles, construction and renovation of objects of public transport infrastructure and conduct of public transport surveys. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Toetus avalikule liiniveole </eesti>
<inglise>Subsidies to public regular services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigieelarvest toetatakse avalikku liinivedu, mida korraldatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Subsidies from the state budget shall be granted to regular public services which are organised on: </inglise>
<eesti>1) riigisisesel rongiliinil, v&auml;lja arvatud linnasisesel v&otilde;i muul riigisisesel rongiliinil, kui s&otilde;itja s&otilde;idu l&auml;hte- ja sihtpunkt asuvad &uuml;he linna piires; </eesti>
<inglise>1) domestic train lines, except urban or other domestic train lines where the points of departure and destination of passengers are located within the one city; </inglise>
<eesti>2) maakonna bussiliinil ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 6 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud juhul kaugliinil; </eesti>
<inglise>2) county bus lines and, in the case specified in subsection 6 (3) of this Act, long-distance lines; </inglise>
<eesti>(07.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.02.2001 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </inglise>
<eesti>3) Eesti mandri ja saarte ning v&auml;ikesaarte vahelisel, Saaremaa ja Hiiumaa vahelisel ning Saaremaa ja Saare maakonna haldusterritooriumil asuvate v&auml;ikesaarte vahelisel laeva-, v&auml;ikelaeva- v&otilde;i parvlaevaliinil; </eesti>
<inglise>3) ship, small ship and ferry lines which connect the Estonian mainland with the islands and small islands, the island of Saaremaa with the island of Hiiumaa and the island of Saaremaa with the small islands located within the administrative territory of Saare county; </inglise>
<eesti>4) Eesti mandri ja saarte ning v&auml;ikesaarte vahelisel, Saaremaa ja Hiiumaa vahelisel ning Saaremaa ja Saare maakonna haldusterritooriumil asuvate v&auml;ikesaarte vahelisel lennuliinil. </eesti>
<inglise>4) air lines which connect the Estonian mainland with the islands and small islands, the island of Saaremaa with the island of Hiiumaa and the island of Saaremaa with the small islands located within the administrative territory of Saare county. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse eelarvest toetatakse avalikku liinivedu, mida korraldatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Subsidies from the budgets of local governments shall be granted to regular public services organised on: </inglise>
<eesti>1) linnasisesel rongiliinil v&otilde;i muul riigisisesel rongiliinil, kui s&otilde;itja s&otilde;idu l&auml;hte- ja sihtpunkt asuvad &uuml;he linna piires; </eesti>
<inglise>1) urban train lines or other domestic train lines where the points of departure and destination of passengers are located within one city; </inglise>
<eesti>2) linna bussi-, trammi- ja trollibussiliinil ning valla bussiliinil, samuti k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 5 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud juhul maakonna bussiliinil ja &sect; 6 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud juhul kaugliinil; </eesti>
<inglise>2) urban bus, tram and trolleybus lines and rural municipality bus lines and county bus lines in the case specified in subsection 5 (3) and long-distance lines in the case specified in subsection 6 (3) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>(07.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.02.2001 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </inglise>
<eesti>3) valla- v&otilde;i linnasisesel laeva-, v&auml;ikelaeva- v&otilde;i parvlaevaliinil. </eesti>
<inglise>3) rural municipality or urban ship, small ship and ferry lines. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse eelarve tulubaas on ebapiisav, katab riik omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse taotlusel riigieelarvest k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud avaliku liiniveo toetuse puuduj&auml;&auml;va osa t&auml;ies ulatuses v&otilde;i osaliselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the revenue base of a local government budget is insufficient to cover support to public regular services specified in subsection (2) of this section, the state shall cover, at the request of the local government, the deficit of the subsidies to public regular services wholly or partly from the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud juhtudel v&otilde;ib riigieelarvest antav toetus moodustada kuni 70 protsenti veokuludest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the cases specified in subsection (1) of this section, the subsidies granted from the state budget may total up to 70 per cent of the cost of transport. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 3 nimetatud laeva-, v&auml;ikelaeva- v&otilde;i parvlaevaliine v&otilde;ib riigieelarvest toetada tasemeni, kus s&otilde;itja s&otilde;idupileti hind saab v&otilde;rdseks niisama pika maanteel&otilde;igu l&auml;bimiseks tehtavate kulutustega, mida arvestatakse maakonna bussiliini keskmise s&otilde;idukilomeetri tariifi j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Subsidies from the state budget may be granted to the ship, small ship and ferry lines specified in clause (1) 3) of this section up to the level where the ticket price paid by a passenger equals the costs incurred in making a journey of the same length by road which shall be calculated on the basis of the average tariff per kilometre of a county bus line. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Avaliku liiniveo toetamine riigieelarvest </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of subsidies to public regular services from state budget </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigieelarvest avaliku liiniveo toetamist kavandades arvestatakse eelmiste aastate statistilisi ning k&auml;esolevaks ja j&auml;rgmiseks aastaks kavandatavaid liiniveokulude andmeid, samuti j&auml;rgmisi statistilisi ja kavandatavaid andmeid ning riiklikest programmidest tulenevaid meetmeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the planning of subsidies from the state budget to public regular services, the statistical data of the previous years and the data planned for the current and following year concerning the costs of regular services and the following statistical and planned data and measures arising from national programs shall be taken into consideration: </inglise>
<eesti>1) liinit&ouml;&ouml;mahtu, s&otilde;itjate arvu ja s&otilde;itjak&auml;ivet; </eesti>
<inglise>1) regular transport volume, number of passengers and passenger turnover; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tarbijahinna indeksi muutumist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) changes in the consumer price index; </inglise>
<eesti>3) maksude laekumisest tulenevat riigieelarve tulubaasi muutumist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) changes in the revenue base of the state budget arising from revenue from taxation; </inglise>
<eesti>4) s&otilde;itjak&auml;ibes arvestatavat &uuml;histranspordi osat&auml;htsuse muutumist; </eesti>
<inglise>4) changes in the role of public transport calculated as passenger turnover; </inglise>
<eesti>5) omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste eelarve tulubaasi muutumist; </eesti>
<inglise>5) changes in the revenue base of local government budgets; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kohalikule avalikule liiniveole riigieelarvest taotletava rahalise toetuse suurust; </eesti>
<inglise>6) amount of financial support to local public regular services requested form the state budget; </inglise>
<eesti>7) liiklusohutuse, keskkonna- ja tervisekaitse ning sotsiaalse ja regionaalse arengu riiklike programmide alusel rakendatavaid meetmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>7) measures applied on the basis of national programs concerning traffic safety, environmental and health protection and social and regional development; </inglise>
<eesti>8) teisi asjaolusid, millel on vahetu seos &uuml;histranspordi osat&auml;htsuse muutumisest tuleneva m&otilde;juga &uuml;hiskonna majanduslikule ja sotsiaalsele arengule. </eesti>
<inglise>8) other circumstances directly related to the effect which the change in the role of public transport has on the economic and social development of the society. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 3 nimetatud maksud on mootors&otilde;iduki- ja mootorik&uuml;tuseaktsiis ning muud seaduse alusel ainult vedajale v&otilde;i s&otilde;iduki omanikule v&otilde;i valdajale kehtestatud riiklikud maksud, l&otilde;ivud ja tasud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The taxes specified in clause (3) 1) of this section are the motor vehicle and motor fuel excise duty and other state taxes, levies and fees imposed exclusively on the carrier, or the owner or possessor of a vehicle on the basis of law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Toetus &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukite soetamiseks v&otilde;i nende &uuml;mberkohandamiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Subsidies for acquisition or reconstruction of public transport vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigieelarves v&otilde;ib ette n&auml;ha investeeringutoetuse &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukite soetamiseks v&otilde;i nende &uuml;mberkohandamiseks j&auml;rgmistel juhtudel: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Investment subsidies for the acquisition or reconstruction of public transport vehicles may be prescribed in the state budget in the following cases: </inglise>
<eesti>1) suure s&otilde;itjatevooga linnu ja nende l&auml;hipiirkonda avalikul liiniveol teenindavate busside, trammide ja trollibusside soetamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the acquisition of busses, trams and trolleybusses for the provision of public regular services in cities with significant passenger flows and in the immediate vicinity of such cities; </inglise>
<eesti>2) riigisiseseks s&otilde;itjateveoks vajaliku raudteeveeremi soetamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the acquisition of rolling stock necessary for the domestic carriage of passengers; </inglise>
<eesti>3) Eesti mandri ja saarte ning v&auml;ikesaarte vaheliseks, Saaremaa ja Hiiumaa vaheliseks ning Saaremaa ja Saare maakonna haldusterritooriumil asuvate v&auml;ikesaarte vaheliseks &uuml;henduseks vajalike laevade, v&auml;ikelaevade ja parvlaevade soetamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the acquisition of ships, small ships and ferries necessary for the provision of a connection between the Estonian mainland and the islands and small islands, the island of Saaremaa and the island of Hiiumaa and the island of Saaremaa and the small islands located within the administrative territory of Saare county; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukitena kasutatavate invas&otilde;idukite soetamiseks v&otilde;i &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukite kohandamiseks puuetega inimeste veoks. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the acquisition of public transport vehicles intended for the carriage of disabled persons or reconstruction of public transport vehicles for the carriage of disabled persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud juhtudel etten&auml;htud toetus v&otilde;ib moodustada &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukite maksumusest nende hanke korral v&otilde;i &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukite &uuml;mberkohandamise maksumusest: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Subsidies prescribed in the cases specified in subsection (1) of this section may total the following percentage of the cost of the acquired public transport vehicles or of the cost of the reconstructed public transport vehicles: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kuni 60 protsenti busside, trammide ja trollibusside hanke korral; </eesti>
<inglise>1) up to 60 per cent in the event of acquisition of busses, trams or trolleybusses; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kuni 75 protsenti s&otilde;itjateveo raudteeveeremi ning laevade, v&auml;ikelaevade ja parvlaevade ning &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukitena kasutatavate invas&otilde;idukite hanke korral; </eesti>
<inglise>2) up to 75 per cent in the event of acquisition of rolling stock intended for the carriage of passengers, of ships, small ships and ferries, and of public transport vehicles intended for the carriage of disabled persons; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kuni 100 protsenti &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukite puuetega inimeste veoks &uuml;mberkohandamise maksumusest. </eesti>
<inglise>3) up to 100 per cent of the cost of reconstruction of public transport vehicles for the carriage of disabled persons. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Toetus &uuml;histranspordi infrastruktuuri objektide rajamiseks ja uuendamiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Subsidies for construction or renovation of objects of public transport infrastructure </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigieelarves v&otilde;ib ette n&auml;ha investeeringutoetuse j&auml;rgmiste avalikku liinivedu teenindavate &uuml;histranspordi infrastruktuuri objektide rajamiseks v&otilde;i uuendamiseks: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Investment subsidies may be prescribed in the state budget for the construction or renovation of the following objects of public transport infrastructure which provide services to public regular services: </inglise>
<eesti>1) suure s&otilde;itjatevooga linnades asuvad eri veoliike teenindavad reisiterminalid, &uuml;leriigilise v&otilde;i regionaalse t&auml;htsusega raudtee- ja bussijaamad ning Eesti saartel, v&auml;ikesaartel ja saartega &uuml;henduse pidamiseks Eesti mandril asuvad mere- v&otilde;i j&otilde;esadama- ja lennujaamarajatised (reisiterminalid, kaid, t&otilde;usu-maandumisrajad jm infrastruktuuriobjektid); </eesti>
<inglise>1) passenger terminals providing services to different modes of transport located in cities with significant passenger flows, railway and bus stations of national or regional importance, and sea, river and airport constructions (passenger terminals, berths, runways and other infrastructure facilities) which are located on Estonian islands or small islands or on the Estonian mainland and are intended for the provision of a connection between the mainland and the islands; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;leriigilise ja regionaalse t&auml;htsusega &uuml;histranspordi informatsiooni- ja sides&uuml;steemid. </eesti>
<inglise>2) public transport information and communication systems of national or regional importance. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud juhtudel etten&auml;htud toetus v&otilde;ib moodustada: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The subsidies prescribed in the cases specified in subsection (1) of this section may total: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kuni 75 protsenti punktis 1 nimetatud projektide maksumusest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) up to 75 per cent of the cost of the projects specified in clause 1); </inglise>
<eesti>2) kuni 100 protsenti punktis 2 nimetatud projektide maksumusest. </eesti>
<inglise>2) up to 100 per cent of the cost of the projects specified in clause 2). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Toetus &uuml;histranspordiuuringute korraldamiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Subsidies for conduct of public transport survey </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;leriigilise v&otilde;i regionaalse t&auml;htsusega &uuml;histranspordiuuringu korraldamiseks n&auml;hakse riigieelarves ette toetus, millega kaetakse kuni 100 protsenti uuringu maksumusest. </eesti>
<inglise>Subsidies shall be prescribed in the state budget for the conduct of a public transport survey of national or regional importance which shall cover up to 100 per cent of the cost of the survey. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;histranspordi toetamise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for support of public transport </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigieelarvest avaliku liiniveo, &uuml;histranspordi infrastruktuuri objektide rajamise ja uuendamise, &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukite soetamise ning &uuml;histranspordiuuringute toetamise korra kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall establish the procedure for allocation of subsidies to public regular services, for construction or renovation of objects of public transport infrastructure, for acquisition of public transport vehicles and for support to the conduct of public transport surveys from the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud kord reguleerib toetuste vajaduse arvestust, omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste ja maavalitsuste asjakohaste taotluste esitamist ja koondamist, riigieelarve eeln&otilde;usse asjakohaste s&auml;tete kavandamist ning riigieelarves etten&auml;htud toetuste jaotamist ja nende kasutamise kontrollimist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The procedure specified in subsection (1) of this section regulates the calculation of the need for subsidies, submission of corresponding applications by local governments and county governments and the consolidation of the applications, planning of the corresponding articles of the draft state budget, distribution of the subsidies prescribed in the state budget and the supervision of the use thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse eelarvest &uuml;histranspordi toetamise korra kehtestab valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for allocation of subsidies to public transport from a local government budget shall be established by a rural municipality or city council. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklikust investeeringust toetatava &uuml;histranspordiprojekti elluviimiseks korraldatav avalik pakkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Public tender for carrying out public transport projects supported by state investments </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 17-19 nimetatud &uuml;histranspordiprojekti elluviimiseks korraldatakse avalik pakkumine riigihangete seaduses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Public tenders shall be organised for carrying out the public transport projects specified in &sect;&sect; 17-19 of this Act pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Public Procurement Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Toetusraha tagastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Return of subsidies </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riikliku toetuse saaja tagastab toetusraha t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i osaliselt v&otilde;i toetuse maksmine peatatakse, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A party which received a state subsidy shall return the subsidy in whole or in part, or the payment of the subsidy shall be suspended if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) toetuse andmise otsus p&otilde;hineb toetuse saaja esitatud mittet&auml;ielikul, eba&otilde;igel v&otilde;i eksitaval teabel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the decision on grant of the subsidy is based on incomplete, inaccurate or misleading information submitted by the party which received the subsidy; </inglise>
<eesti>2) toetuse eraldamise v&otilde;i maksmise v&otilde;i toetuse kasutamise kontrollimise kohta on esitatud vale v&otilde;i puudulik informatsioon ning kui see on oluliselt m&otilde;jutanud toetuse saamist v&otilde;i selleks kehtestatud tingimusi; </eesti>
<inglise>2) false or insufficient information was submitted concerning the allocation, payment or supervision of the use of the state subsidy and if the submission of such information significantly influenced the grant of the subsidy or the conditions established therefor; </inglise>
<eesti>3) toetuse saaja on keeldunud esitamast informatsiooni, dokumente v&otilde;i tegeliku piletitulu v&otilde;i muid andmeid, mida on vaja toetuse m&auml;&auml;ramise v&otilde;i toetuse kasutamise kontrollimise kohta otsuse tegemiseks v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>3) the party which received the state subsidy refuses to submit information, documents, data on actual revenue from the sale of tickets or other data needed for the making of the decision on the grant of the subsidy or supervision of the use thereof, or </inglise>
<eesti>4) kui toetust ei ole kasutatud sihip&auml;raselt. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the state subsidy is not used for the intended purpose. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui riikliku toetuse kasutamise kohta esitatavaid n&otilde;udeid on muul viisil eiratud, v&otilde;ib toetuse v&otilde;i selle osa tagasi n&otilde;uda ning maksmata osa v&otilde;ib t&uuml;histada v&otilde;i selle v&auml;ljamaksmise peatada. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The return of a state subsidy or a part thereof may be required and the part not paid may be revoked or its payment suspended if the requirements set for the use of the state subsidy are disregarded in any other manner. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 nimetatud juhtudel riiklik toetus t&uuml;histatakse, toetuse maksmine peatatakse ja toetusraha tagastatakse toetuse eraldanud ametiasutuse v&otilde;i seadusega v&otilde;i seaduse alusel vastuv&otilde;etud &otilde;igusaktiga nimetatud muu p&auml;deva ametiasutuse korralduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the cases specified in subsections (1) or (2) of this section, the state subsidy shall be revoked, payment thereof shall be suspended or the subsidy shall be returned on the basis of an order issued by the agency which allocated the subsidy or by other competent agencies appointed by an Act or other legal instruments adopted pursuant to an Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Uuml;histranspordi toetusraha tagasimaksmise korra kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The procedure for the return of subsidy funds for public transport shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;histranspordi arengukava </eesti>
<inglise>Public transport development plan </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;histranspordi arengukava </eesti>
<inglise>Public transport development plan </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;histransporti arendatakse pikaajalise riikliku arengukava alusel, mille kinnitab Riigikogu oma otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Public transport shall be developed on the basis of a long-term national development plan approved by a resolution of the Riigikogu (2). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;histranspordi pikaajaline riiklik arengukava koostatakse, l&auml;htudes s&auml;&auml;stva arengu seaduse (RT I 1995, 31, 384; 1997, 48, 772; 1999, 29, 398; 2000, 54, 348) &sect;-st 12 ning keskkonnakaitse, regionaalse arengu, liiklusohutuse ja sotsiaalse arengu programmidest ning teistest riiklikest programmidest, mille eesm&auml;rgid on seotud &uuml;histranspordi arendamisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The long-term public transport development plan shall be prepared on the basis of &sect; 12 of the Sustainable Development Act (RT I 1995, 31, 384; 1997, 48, 772; 1999, 29, 398; 2000, 54, 348), programs concerning environmental protection, regional development, traffic safety, social development and other national programs the objectives of which are related to the development of public transport. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;histranspordi pikaajaline riiklik arengukava peab sisaldama: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The long-term national public transport development plan shall include: </inglise>
<eesti>1) andmeid &uuml;histranspordi toetamiseks riigieelarvest etten&auml;htud sihtotstarbelise toetuse arvestusliku vajaduse kohta, mis tuleneb &uuml;histranspordi osat&auml;htsuse kavandatavast muutmisest ning eelarve tulubaasi muutumisest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) data concerning the calculated need for subsidies for specific purposes prescribed in the state budget for the support of public transport which arises from the planned changes to the role of public transport and to the revenue base of the budget; </inglise>
<eesti>2) nende &otilde;iguslike, majanduslike, sotsiaalsete ja tehniliste abin&otilde;ude loetelu, mis suurendavad &uuml;histranspordi konkurentsiv&otilde;imet; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a list of legal, economic, social and technical measures to improve the competitive position of public transport; </inglise>
<eesti>3) muude &uuml;histranspordi arengut m&otilde;jutavate tegurite loetelu. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a list of other factors which influence the development of public transport. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;histransporditeenuse hind </eesti>
<inglise>Prices of Public Transport Services </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;histransporditeenuse hinna ja tariifi ning s&otilde;idupiletihinna kehtestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Establishment of prices, tariffs and ticket prices for public transport services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kommertsliiniveo ja juhuveo teenuste hinna kehtestab vedaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The service prices in commercial regular services and occasional services shall be established by the carriers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avaliku liiniveo s&otilde;idukilomeetri tariifi v&otilde;i s&otilde;idupiletihinna kehtestab: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The tariffs per kilometre or ticket prices in public regular services shall be established by: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teede- ja sideminister v&otilde;i tema volitatud ametiasutus raudteeliikluses korraldataval s&otilde;itjateveol, v&auml;lja arvatud linnasisene vedu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the Minister of Transport and Communications or an agency authorised by the Minister in the carriage of passengers organised by means of railway traffic, except in urban carriage; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teede- ja sideminister v&otilde;i tema volitatud ametiasutus laeva-, v&auml;ikelaeva- ja parvlaeva- ning lennuliikluses korraldataval maakondadevahelisel ja &uuml;leriigilisel s&otilde;itjateveol; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the Minister of Transport and Communications or an agency authorised by the Minister in the inter-county or national carriage of passengers organised by means of ship, small ship, ferry and air traffic; </inglise>
<eesti>3) maavanem bussi-, laeva-, v&auml;ikelaeva- ja parvlaeva- ning lennuliikluses maakonnasisesel s&otilde;itjateveol; </eesti>
<inglise>3) county governors in the intra-county carriage of passengers organised by means of bus, ship, small ship, ferry and air traffic; </inglise>
<eesti>4) valla- ja linnavolikogu v&otilde;i nende volitatud ametiasutus bussi-, trammi-, trollibussi- ning laeva-, v&auml;ikelaeva- ja parvlaevaliikluses valla- v&otilde;i linnasisesel s&otilde;itjateveol; </eesti>
<inglise>4) rural municipality and city councils or agencies authorised thereby in the carriage of passengers organised by means of bus, tram, trolleybus, ship, small ship and ferry traffic within the rural municipality or city; </inglise>
<eesti>5) linnavolikogu v&otilde;i tema volitatud ametiasutus raudteeliikluses korraldataval linnasisesel s&otilde;itjateveol. </eesti>
<inglise>5) city councils and agencies authorised thereby in the urban carriage of passengers organised by means of railway traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Taksoveo s&otilde;idukilomeetri ja s&otilde;idutunni tariifid ning muude teenuste hinnad (edaspidi taksoteenuste tariifid) kehtestab vedaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The tariffs per kilometre and per hour in taxi service and the prices for other services provided by taxi service (hereinafter prices for taxi service) shall be established by the carriers. </inglise>
<eesti>Maanteeliikluses osutatavate taksoteenuste tariifide kehtestamisel ning rakendamisel peab vedaja j&auml;rgima j&auml;rgmisi n&otilde;udeid: </eesti>
<inglise>In the establishing and application of tariffs for taxi service provided in road traffic, the carriers shall adhere to the following requirements: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&otilde;ik vedaja kehtestatud taksoteenuste tariifid peavad olema programmeeritud taksole paigaldatud taksomeetrisse, mis on m&otilde;&otilde;teseaduse (RT I 1994, 71, 1224; 2000, 71, 442) n&otilde;uete kohaselt saanud t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnituse ja taadeldud, mootors&otilde;idukiga adapteeritud (edaspidi kohandatud) ning varustatud sellele taksomeetrile sobiva printeriga; </eesti>
<inglise>1) all tariffs for taxi service established by a carrier shall be programmed into a taxi meter which shall have type approval and be collated pursuant to the requirements of the Metrology Act (RT I 1994, 71, 1224; 2000, 71, 442), be adapted for a corresponding motor vehicle and equipped with a printer suitable for such meter; </inglise>
<eesti>2) taksojuht peab andma taksoteenuse kasutajale taksomeetri printeril tr&uuml;kitud kviitungi, millele on m&auml;rgitud vedaja nimi ja registrikood, s&otilde;iduki registreerimism&auml;rk, teenuse osutamise kuup&auml;ev ning alguse ja l&otilde;pu kellaaeg, osutatud teenuse maht ja maksumus k&otilde;igi kasutatud tariifide l&otilde;ikes ning &uuml;ldmaksumus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a taxi driver shall provide the user of taxi service with a receipt printed out on the printer connected to the taxi meter which shall set out the name and registry code of the carrier, the registration plate, date of provision of service, time of beginning and end of provision of service, volume and cost of the provided service by all used tariffs, and the total cost; </inglise>
<eesti>3) taksol v&otilde;ib kasutada k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 1 nimetatud n&otilde;uetele vastavat taksomeetrit ka ilma printerita tingimusel, et taksomeetrisse programmeeritud taksoteenuste tariifide &uuml;mberl&uuml;litamine toimub &uuml;ksnes automaatselt. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a taxi meter in compliance with the requirements specified in clause 1) of this section may be used without a printer in a taxi on condition that the tariffs programmed into the taxi meter switch only automatically. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellel juhul peab taksojuht andma taksoteenuse kasutajale vedaja rekvisiitidega blanketil k&auml;sitsi t&auml;idetud kviitungi osutatud taksoteenuse kuup&auml;eva, kellaaja ja &uuml;ldmaksumuse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>In such event, a taxi driver shall provide the user of taxi service with a receipt filled out by hand on a form bearing the requisite information concerning the carrier and which sets out the date, time and total cost of the taxi service provided. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Taksomeetri kohandamine on taksomeetri mootors&otilde;idukile paigaldamine, reguleerimine ja plommimine selleks vastavat luba omava ettev&otilde;tja poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) "Adaption of taxi meter" means the installation of a taxi meter on a motor vehicle and the adaption and sealing thereof by an undertaking which holds a corresponding licence. </inglise>
<eesti>Taksomeetreid v&otilde;ib kohandada ettev&otilde;tja, kelle on m&otilde;&otilde;teseaduse &sect;-s 13 nimetatud akrediteerimisasutus tunnistanud erialaselt p&auml;devaks seda t&ouml;&ouml;d tegema. </eesti>
<inglise>Taxi meters may be adjusted by undertakings which are approved by the accreditation institution specified in &sect; 13 of the Metrology Act to be professionally competent to perform such operation. </inglise>
<eesti>Taksomeetrite kohandamise korra kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Transport and Communications shall establish the procedure for the adaption of taxi meters. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Rahvusvahelise liiniveo teenuste hinnad kehtestab vedaja Eesti Vabariigi v&auml;lislepingut j&auml;rgides. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The prices for international regular services shall be established by the carriers in adherence with international agreements entered into by the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;idusoodustused </eesti>
<inglise>Travel Fare Concessions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;idusoodustuse m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of travel fare concession </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&otilde;idusoodustus on teatava kategooria s&otilde;itjale seadusega v&otilde;i seaduse alusel kehtestatud korras antud &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A "travel fare concession" means the right granted to particular categories of passengers by law or pursuant to the procedure established by law to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) s&otilde;ita &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukis tasuta v&otilde;i osalise tasu eest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) use a public transport vehicle without charge or for a reduced charge; </inglise>
<eesti>2) s&otilde;ita &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukis t&auml;ishinna eest ning saada enne v&otilde;i hiljem osalist v&otilde;i t&auml;ielikku rahalist h&uuml;vitist. </eesti>
<inglise>2) use a public transport vehicle for a full price and receive partial or full monetary compensation therefor beforehand or afterwards. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 1 nimetatud s&otilde;idusoodustusele &otilde;igust omav isik peab &uuml;hiss&otilde;iduki juhi v&otilde;i muu kontrollimis&otilde;igusega ametiisiku n&otilde;udmisel esitama s&otilde;idusoodustuse &otilde;igust t&otilde;endava dokumendi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person who is entitled to a travel fare concession specified in clause (1) 1) of this section shall present, at the request of the driver of a public transport vehicle or other persons with inspection right, a document certifying his or her right to the travel fare concession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;itjale s&otilde;idusoodustuse h&uuml;vitamine riigieelarvest </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation of travel fare concession to passengers from state budget </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&otilde;idusoodustuseks riigieelarvest eraldatud rahaliste vahendite arvel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 25 l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 2 alusel makstava h&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;rad n&auml;hakse ette seadusega v&otilde;i seaduse alusel vastuv&otilde;etava muu &otilde;igusaktiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The amounts of compensation for travel fare concessions paid out of the funds appropriated from the state budget pursuant to clause 25 (1) 2) of this Act shall be prescribed by an Act or other legal instruments adopted pursuant to an Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud h&uuml;vitise maksmise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus v&otilde;i tema volitatud minister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The procedure for payment of the concessions specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be established by the Government of the Republic or a Minister authorised by the Government. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasuta s&otilde;it riigisisesel liiniveol </eesti>
<inglise>Free transportation in domestic regular services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigisisesel liinil (kaasa arvatud kommertsliin) raudtee-, maantee- ja veeliikluses on vedaja kohustatud tasuta vedama: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) On domestic lines in railway, road and waterway traffic (including commercial lines), carriers are required to carry without charge: </inglise>
<eesti>1) eelkooliealisi lapsi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) pre-school children; </inglise>
<eesti>2) puudega lapsi, s&uuml;gava puudega 16-aastaseid ja vanemaid isikuid ning n&auml;gemispuudega isikut saatvat juhtkoera; </eesti>
<inglise>2) disabled children, persons over 16 years of age with profound disability and guide dogs who accompany blind persons; </inglise>
<eesti>3) Vabaduss&otilde;ja veterane. </eesti>
<inglise>3) veterans of the Estonian War of Independence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud kategooria s&otilde;itjate tasuta s&otilde;itu vedajale ei h&uuml;vitata. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Carriers are not compensated for the free transportation of the categories of passengers specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Kommertsliiniveol kehtivad s&otilde;idusoodustused </eesti>
<inglise>Travel fare concessions in force in commercial regular services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;evases &otilde;ppevormis &otilde;ppivale &otilde;pilasele ja statsionaarses &otilde;ppevormis &otilde;ppivale &uuml;li&otilde;pilasele (edaspidi &otilde;pilane ja &uuml;li&otilde;pilane) h&uuml;vitatakse kommertsliinil (v&auml;lja arvatud lennuliin) s&otilde;idu kulu riigieelarvest s&otilde;idusoodustuseks eraldatud rahaliste vahendite arvel kuni 100 protsenti pileti t&auml;ishinnast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) On commercial lines (except air lines), school pupils enrolled in daytime study and students in full-time study (hereinafter school pupils and students) shall be compensated for the travel expenses out of the funds appropriated from the state budget for the payment of travel fare concessions in the amount of up to 100 per cent of the full price of a ticket. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;idukulu iga-aastase h&uuml;vitamise ulatuse m&auml;&auml;rab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The annual extent of compensation for travel expenses shall be determined by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(07.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.02.2001 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 k&auml;sitletud s&otilde;idukulu h&uuml;vitamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The procedure for compensation for travel expenses specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Valla- ja linnavolikogu v&otilde;ivad k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud h&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;ra suurendada oma eelarvest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Rural municipality and city councils may increase the extent of compensation specified in subsection (1) of this section out of their budgets. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalikul liiniveol kehtivad s&otilde;idusoodustused </eesti>
<inglise>Travel fare concessions in force in public regular services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avalikul liiniveol antakse maantee- ja veeliikluses ning raudteeliikluses linnasisesel v&otilde;i muul riigisisesel rongiliinil, kui s&otilde;itja s&otilde;idu l&auml;hte- ja sihtpunkt asuvad &uuml;he linna piires, &otilde;pilasele ja &uuml;li&otilde;pilasele, s&uuml;gava puudega isiku saatjale, puudega lapse saatjale ja Vabaduss&otilde;ja veterani saatjale s&otilde;idusoodustust kuni 50 protsenti pileti t&auml;ishinnast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In public regular services provided in road and waterway traffic on urban or other domestic train lines where points of departure and destination of passengers are located within the limits of one city, school pupils and students, persons who accompany persons with a profound disability, persons who accompany disabled children or persons who accompany veterans of the Estonian War of Independence shall be granted travel fare concessions in the amount of up to 50 per cent of the full price of a ticket. </inglise>
<eesti>Iga-aastase s&otilde;idusoodustuse ulatuse m&auml;&auml;rab: </eesti>
<inglise>The extent of annual travel fare concessions shall be determined: </inglise>
<eesti>1) maanteeliikluses valla- ja linnavolikogu valla- v&otilde;i linnaliinile ning maavanem maakonnaliinile; </eesti>
<inglise>1) in road traffic - by a rural municipality or city council for rural municipality or urban lines and by county governors for county lines; </inglise>
<eesti>2) veeliikluses teede- ja sideminister k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 15 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 3 nimetatud laeva-, v&auml;ikelaeva- ja parvlaevaliinile; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in waterway traffic - by the Minister of Transport and Communications for the ship, small ship and ferry lines specified in clause 15 (1) 3) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) raudteeliikluses linnavolikogu k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 15 l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 1 nimetatud rongiliinile. </eesti>
<inglise>3) in railway traffic - by city councils for train lines specified in clause 15 (2) 1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud soodustus kaetakse toetuste arvel, mis on sellele avalikule liiniveole eraldatud linna- v&otilde;i vallaeelarvest v&otilde;i riigieelarvest k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 15 kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The concession specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be covered out of the subsidies allocated to such regular services from the city or rural municipality budget or state budget pursuant to &sect;15 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Valla- ja linnavolikogu v&otilde;ivad lisaks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 27 ning k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatule kehtestada avalikul liiniveol oma eelarvest s&otilde;idusoodustusi veel teatava kategooria s&otilde;itjatele, samuti suurendada s&otilde;idusoodustuse m&auml;&auml;ra. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In addition to the provisions of &sect; 27 of this Act and subsection (1) of this section, rural municipality and city councils may establish travel fare concessions in public regular services out of their budgets to particular categories of passengers and increase the amount of travel fare concessions. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Valla- ja linnavolikogu v&otilde;ivad avalikule liiniveole riigieelarvest eraldatud toetuste arvel anda s&otilde;idusoodustusi nende m&auml;&auml;ratud teatud kategooria s&otilde;itjatele v&otilde;i lisaks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud m&auml;&auml;rale &uuml;ksnes siis, kui see on koosk&otilde;lastatud riigiasutusega, kelle kaudu liinivedu riigieelarvest toetatakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Rural municipality and city councils may grant travel fare concessions out of subsidies allocated from the state budget to public regular services for particular categories of passengers determined by the rural municipality and city councils, or to grant travel fare concessions in addition to the amount provided for in subsection (1) of this section only with the approval of the state agency through which the support is allocated from the state budget for the public regular services. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Avalikul liiniveol h&uuml;vitatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 15 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 1 nimetatud rongiliinil ja &sect; 15 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 4 nimetatud lennuliinil &otilde;pilasele ja &uuml;li&otilde;pilasele s&otilde;idukulu riigieelarvest s&otilde;idusoodustuseks eraldatud rahaliste vahendite arvel kuni 50 protsenti pileti t&auml;ishinnast. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In public regular services on train lines specified in clause 15 (1) 1) of this Act and on air lines specified in clause 15 (1) 4) of this Act, school pupils and students shall be compensated for the travel expenses out of the funds appropriated for the payment of travel fare concessions from the state budget in the amount of up to 50 per cent of the full price of a ticket. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;idukulu iga-aastase h&uuml;vitamise ulatuse m&auml;&auml;rab ja h&uuml;vitamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The annual extent of compensation for travel expenses shall be determined by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(07.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.02.2001 entered into force 01.03.2001 - RT I 2001, 18, 85) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Vedaja antavad s&otilde;idusoodustused </eesti>
<inglise>Travel fare concessions granted by carrier </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avalikul liiniveol v&otilde;ib vedaja anda lisaks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 27 ja 29 nimetatud isikutele s&otilde;idusoodustusi ka teistele s&otilde;itjatele v&otilde;i suurendada soodustuse m&auml;&auml;ra &uuml;ksnes teise lepingupoole loal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In public regular services, carriers may grant travel fare concessions to other categories of passengers in addition to the persons specified in &sect; 27 and 29 of this Act or increase the amount of concessions only with the consent of the other party to the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahvusvahelisel liiniveol v&otilde;ib vedaja anda soodustusi, j&auml;rgides Eesti Vabariigi v&auml;lislepingutest tulenevaid n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In international regular services, carriers may grant travel fare concessions in adherence with the requirements arising from international agreements entered into by the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kommertsliiniveol ja taksoveol vedaja antud soodustused h&uuml;vitamisele ei kuulu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Concessions granted by carriers in commercial regular services and taxi service are not subject to compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;itjateveo tegevusluba, s&otilde;idukikaart ja liiniluba maanteeliikluses </eesti>
<inglise>Licence for Carriage of Passengers, Vehicle Card and Line Permit in Road Traffic </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;itjateveo tegevusluba ja s&otilde;idukikaart </eesti>
<inglise>Licence for carriage of passengers and vehicle card </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maanteeliikluses korraldatava s&otilde;itjateveo tegevusloana (edaspidi tegevusluba) k&auml;sitatakse &uuml;histranspordiluba ja taksoveoluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Public transport licences and taxi licences are deemed to be licences for the carriage of passengers in road traffic (hereinafter licence). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;histranspordiluba t&otilde;endab vedaja &otilde;igust: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A public transport licence certifies the right of a carrier to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) korraldada juhuvedu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) organise occasional services; </inglise>
<eesti>2) taotleda &otilde;igust korraldada liinivedu k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 32 nimetatud liiniloa v&otilde;i lepingu alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>2) apply for a right to organise regular services on the basis of a line permit specified in &sect; 32 of this Act or on the basis of a contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Taksoveoluba t&otilde;endab vedaja &otilde;igust korraldada taksovedu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A taxi licence certifies the right of a carrier to organise taxi service. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) S&otilde;idukikaart on tegevusloa alusel vedajale v&auml;ljastatav dokument, mis t&otilde;endab vedaja &otilde;igust kasutada s&otilde;idukikaardile kantud s&otilde;idukit nimetatud tegevusloaga lubatud s&otilde;itjateveol. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) "Vehicle card" means a document granted on the basis of a licence to a carrier which certifies the right of the carrier to use the vehicle entered on the vehicle card for the carriage of passengers permitted by such licence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Liiniveo korraldamise &otilde;igust t&otilde;endavad dokumendid </eesti>
<inglise>Documents which certify right to organise regular services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liiniluba t&otilde;endab vedaja &otilde;igust korraldada kommertsliinivedu (kaasa arvatud eriotstarbeline) liiniloale m&auml;rgitud liinil. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A line permit certifies the right of a carrier to organise commercial regular services (including special commercial regular services) on the line entered on the line permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avaliku teenindamise leping t&otilde;endab vedaja &otilde;igust korraldada avalikku liinivedu (kaasa arvatud eriotstarbeline) &uuml;hel v&otilde;i mitmel liinil v&otilde;i teatava liiniv&otilde;rgu ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A public service contract certifies the right of a carrier to organise public regular services (including special public regular services) on one line or several lines or within an a particular route network. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vedaja ja tellija s&otilde;lmitud eriotstarbelise kommertsliiniveo leping t&otilde;endab vedaja &otilde;igust korraldada eriotstarbelist kommertsliinivedu &uuml;hel v&otilde;i mitmel liinil. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A contract for special commercial regular services entered into between a carrier and an ordering party certifies the right of the carrier to organise special commercial regular services on one line or several lines. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa, s&otilde;idukikaardi ja liiniveo korraldamise &otilde;igust t&otilde;endava dokumendi kohustuslikkus </eesti>
<inglise>Mandatory licence, vehicle card and document which certifies right to organise regular services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tasu eest korraldatav s&otilde;itjatevedu on tegevusloa ja s&otilde;idukikaardita keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Without a licence and vehicle card, it is prohibited to organise fee-charging carriage of passengers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Liinivedu (kaasa arvatud ajutine liinivedu) on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 32 l&otilde;igetes 1-3 nimetatud dokumendita keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Regular services (including temporary regular services) are prohibited without the document specified in subsections 32 (1) -(3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tasu eest korraldatav s&otilde;itjatevedu, mis oma laadilt on v&otilde;rreldav liiniveoga ja mille eesm&auml;rk on osutada teenust liiniveo kasutajatele, on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 32 l&otilde;igetes 1-3 nimetatud dokumendita keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Without the document specified in subsections 32 (1) -(3) of this Act, it is prohibited to organise fee-charging carriage of passengers which is similar to regular services and the aim of which is to provide services to the users of regular services. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa, s&otilde;idukikaardi ja liiniloa andja </eesti>
<inglise>Agencies which grant licences, vehicle cards and line permits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 31 nimetatud tegevuslubasid ja s&otilde;idukikaarte ning &sect;-s 32 nimetatud liinilubasid annavad Teede- ja Sideministeerium, maavalitsus, vallavalitsus ning linnavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Ministry of Transport and Communications, county governments, rural municipality and city governments shall grant the licences and vehicle cards specified in &sect; 31 of this Act and the line permits specified in &sect; 32 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;histranspordiloa ja selle alusel s&otilde;idukikaardi annab vedajale: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Carriers shall be granted public transport licences and vehicle cards on the basis of the licences for: </inglise>
<eesti>1) bussiveoks vedaja registreerimiskoha j&auml;rgne maavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>1) carriage by bus - by the county government of the location of the carrier's registration. </inglise>
<eesti>Tallinnas, Tartus, Narvas, Kohtla-J&auml;rvel ja P&auml;rnus registreeritud vedajale annab loa ja s&otilde;idukikaardi linnavalitsus; </eesti>
<inglise>Carriers registered in Tallinn, Tartu, Narva, Kohtla-J&auml;rve and P&auml;rnu shall be granted licences and vehicle cards by the corresponding city government; </inglise>
<eesti>2) trammi- ja trollibussiveoks vedaja registreerimiskoha j&auml;rgne valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>2) carriage by tram or trolleybus - by the rural municipality or city government of the location of the carrier's registration. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Taksoveoloa ja selle alusel s&otilde;idukikaardi annab vedajale tema registreerimiskoha j&auml;rgne valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Carriers shall be granted taxi licences and vehicle cards on the basis thereof by the rural municipality or city government of the location of the carrier's registration. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Liiniloa annab vedajale, kellel on &uuml;histranspordiluba: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Carriers holding public transport licences shall be granted line permits for: </inglise>
<eesti>1) valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus bussi-, trammi- ja trollibussiveoks valla- v&otilde;i linnaliinil; </eesti>
<inglise>1) carriage by bus, tram or trolleybus on rural municipality or urban lines - by the rural municipality or city government; </inglise>
<eesti>2) maavalitsus bussiveoks maakonnaliinil; </eesti>
<inglise>2) carriage by bus on county lines - by county governments; </inglise>
<eesti>3) Teede- ja Sideministeerium bussiveoks kaugliinil. </eesti>
<inglise>3) carriage by bus on long-distance lines - by the Ministry of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Liiniloa andja korraldab k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 nimetatud liiniveole vedaja valimiseks avaliku konkursi, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Agencies which grant line permits shall organise a public competition to select carriers for the provision of the regular services specified in subsection (4) of this section if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) uue liini avamiseks on tekkinud n&otilde;udlus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) there is demand for the opening of a new line; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vedaja &uuml;histranspordiluba v&otilde;i liiniluba on kehtetuks tunnistatud v&otilde;i vedaja on loobunud liini teenindamisest, kuigi n&otilde;udlus on olemas; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a carrier's public transport licence or line permit is revoked or a carrier refuses to service a line although there is demand for the service; </inglise>
<eesti>3) vedaja ei taotle uut liiniluba liinile, mida ta seni on teenindanud, kuigi n&otilde;udlus on olemas. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a carrier does not apply for a new line permit for a line which the carrier has previously serviced although there is demand for the service. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Avaliku konkursita antakse liiniluba vedajale, kes: </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A carrier shall be granted a line permit without a public competition if the carrier: </inglise>
<eesti>1) taotleb liiniluba tema enda algatusel avatavale liinile; </eesti>
<inglise>1) applies for a line permit to service a line to be opened on the carrier's initiative; </inglise>
<eesti>2) taotleb uut liiniluba liinile, mida ta seni on teenindanud. </eesti>
<inglise>2) applies for a line permit to service a line which the carrier previously has hitherto serviced. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Tegevusloa ja liiniloa v&otilde;ib anda ka k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 alusel moodustatav piirkondlik &uuml;histranspordikeskus. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The regional public transport centres formed pursuant to &sect; 7 of this Act may also grant licences and line permits. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;uded tegevusloa taotlejale v&otilde;i loa omanikule ning vedude eest vastutavale isikule </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements set for applicants for licences, holders of licences and persons responsible for transport operation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusluba antakse isikule, kes vastab k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis esitatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who complies with the requirements set out in this section may be granted a licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusloa taotlejal v&otilde;i loa omanikul peab olema hea majandusseisund. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The applicant for a licence and the holder of a licence shall have a good economic standing. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusloa omaniku registreeritud tegevusala peab olema &uuml;histransporditeenuse osutamine v&otilde;i seda h&otilde;lmav muu tegevus transpordi valdkonnas. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The registered area of activity of the holder of a licence shall be the provision of public transport services or other activity in the area of transport which includes the provision of public transport services. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud tegevusala peab olema registreeritud enne esimese s&otilde;idukikaardi taotluse esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>Such area of activity must be registered before the submission of an application for the first vehicle card. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tegevusloa taotleja v&otilde;i loa omanik peab m&auml;&auml;rama vedude eest vastutava isiku, kes korraldab vedaja veoteenuste osutamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The applicant for a licence or the holder of a licence shall appoint a person responsible for transport operation who shall organise the provision of transport services by the carrier. </inglise>
<eesti>Vedaja v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata ka mitu vedude eest vastutavat isikut. </eesti>
<inglise>A carrier may also appoint several persons responsible for transport operation. </inglise>
<eesti>Vedude eest vastutav isik v&otilde;ib olla f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust vedaja ise. </eesti>
<inglise>A carrier who is a natural person may appoint himself or herself as the person responsible for transport operations. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Vedude eest vastutav isik peab olema teov&otilde;imeline hea mainega isik, kes on ametialaselt p&auml;dev korraldama s&otilde;itjatevedu. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A person responsible for transport operation must have active legal capacity, good reputation and professional competence necessary for the organisation of carriage of passengers. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Tegevusloa andjal on &otilde;igus tegevusloa kehtivusaja jooksul vajaduse korral kontrollida tegevusloa omaniku vastavust k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Agencies which grant licences have the right to check the compliance of the holders of licences with the requirements of this section before the expiry date of the licence if necessary. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa omanik peab sellist kontrolli v&otilde;imaldama. </eesti>
<inglise>The holder of a licence shall allow such checks. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa taotleja ja loa omaniku majandusseisund </eesti>
<inglise>Economic standing of applicant for licence or holder of licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa taotleja v&otilde;i loa omaniku majandusseisund on hea, kui ta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 loetletud andmetele tuginedes t&otilde;estab, et tal on ettev&otilde;tluse alustamiseks ja vedude n&otilde;uetekohaseks korraldamiseks vajalik rahaline seis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The applicant for a licence or the holder of a licence is deemed to have a good economic standing if the applicant or holder can certify on the basis of the data listed in subsection (2) of this section that their financial position is adequate to commence business and organise transport operation according to the requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahalist seisu hinnates v&otilde;etakse arvesse aastaaruanded. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In evaluation of the financial position, annual accounts shall be taken into consideration. </inglise>
<eesti>Aastaaruannete puudumise korral v&otilde;etakse arvesse: </eesti>
<inglise>In the absence of annual accounts, the following shall be taken into consideration: </inglise>
<eesti>1) raha pangakontol ja muud rahalised vahendid ning v&otilde;lgnevused ja laenud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) cash at bank account and other funds, debts and loans; </inglise>
<eesti>2) majandustegevuse stabiilsuse tagamiseks etten&auml;htud vara ja muu vara; </eesti>
<inglise>2) assets available to provide security for the undertaking and other assets; </inglise>
<eesti>3) s&otilde;idukite, kinnistute, seadmete ja varustuse ostukulud v&otilde;i esimesed sissemaksed ja k&auml;ibekapital ning muud kulud. </eesti>
<inglise>3) purchase cost or initial payment for vehicles, registered immovables, plant and equipment, and working capital and other costs. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;hele s&otilde;idukile s&otilde;idukikaardi saamiseks peab &uuml;histranspordiloa omanik t&otilde;endama, et tal on omavahendeid v&auml;hemalt 140 000 krooni ulatuses; iga j&auml;rgmise s&otilde;iduki korral on see summa v&auml;hemalt 80 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order to be granted a vehicle card for one vehicle, the holder of a public transport licence shall certify the existence of own funds in the amount of at least 140 000 kroons, and for each following vehicle at least in the amount of 80 000 kroons. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavahendite olemasolu t&otilde;endamiseks esitab &uuml;histranspordiloa omanik s&otilde;idukikaardi andjale j&auml;rgmised dokumendid: </eesti>
<inglise>In order to certify the existence of own funds, the holder of a public transport licence shall submit the following documents to the agency which grants the vehicle card: </inglise>
<eesti>1) juriidilisest isikust vedaja esitab oma varade ja kohustuste auditeeritud seisu, mille fikseerimisest ei v&otilde;i olla m&ouml;&ouml;dunud rohkem kui kuus kuud. </eesti>
<inglise>1) a carrier who is a legal person shall submit the audited status of the carrier's assets and liabilities which shall be documented not later than six months prior to the submission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Samal eesm&auml;rgil v&otilde;ib s&otilde;idukikaardi andja tunnustada v&otilde;i t&otilde;endusena n&otilde;uda panga v&otilde;i muu asjakohaste volitustega asutuse kinnitust v&otilde;i t&otilde;endit kas garantiikirja v&otilde;i muul samav&auml;&auml;rsel viisil antud kinnituse v&otilde;i t&otilde;endina; </eesti>
<inglise>For the same purpose, the agency which grants a vehicle card may accept or require as proof, confirmation or certification in the form of a letter of guarantee, or confirmation or certification issued in any other equivalent manner by a bank or other agency with appropriate authority; </inglise>
<eesti>2) f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust vedaja esitab panga v&otilde;i muu asjakohaste volitustega asutuse kinnituse v&otilde;i t&otilde;endi kas garantiikirja v&otilde;i muul samav&auml;&auml;rsel viisil antud kinnituse v&otilde;i t&otilde;endina. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a carrier who is a natural person shall submit confirmation or certification in the form of a letter of guarantee or confirmation or certification issued in any other equivalent manner by a bank or other agency with appropriate authority. </inglise>
<eesti>Samal eesm&auml;rgil v&otilde;ib vedaja esitada oma varade ja kohustuste auditeeritud seisu, mille fikseerimisest ei v&otilde;i olla m&ouml;&ouml;dunud rohkem kui kuus kuud. </eesti>
<inglise>For the same purpose, the carrier may submit the audited status of his or her assets and liabilities which shall be documented not later than six months prior to the submission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Vedude eest vastutava isiku maine </eesti>
<inglise>Reputation of person responsible for transport operation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vedude eest vastutava isiku mainet peetakse heaks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The reputation of a person responsible for transport operation is deemed to be good if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teda ei ole kriminaalkorras karistatud v&otilde;i kui karistuse &auml;rakandmisest on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud v&auml;hemalt kolm aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the person has not been punished pursuant to criminal procedure or more than three years have passed from the date on which the person finished the serving of the sentence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tal ei ole &uuml;le kahe haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 58, 608; 92, 825; 95, 843; 2000, 10, 58; 25, 141; 28, 167; 29, 169; 40, 247; 49, 301; 49, 305; 51, 321; 54, 351; 54, 346; 54, 348; 54, 351; 55, 361; 58, 376; 84, 533; 86, 544; 86, 548; 95, 609; 95, 613; 2001, 21, 115; 21, 116; 89, 578) &sect; 31 kohaselt kehtiva haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise, mis on toime pandud t&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;u kasutamise, t&ouml;&ouml;tasustamise, veokorralduse, t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja reguleerimise, liiklusohutuse, s&otilde;idukite ohutuse v&otilde;i keskkonnakaitse valdkonnas, v&otilde;i kui rikkumisest hoolimata ei sea loa andja kahtluse alla tema k&otilde;lblikkust korraldada s&otilde;itjatevedu. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the person has not committed more than two administrative offences in force pursuant to &sect; 31 of the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 58, 608; 92, 825; 95, 843; 2000, 10, 58; 25, 141; 28, 167; 29, 169; 40, 247; 49, 301; 49, 305; 51, 321; 54, 351; 54, 346; 54, 348; 54, 351; 55, 361; 58, 376; 84, 533; 86, 544; 86, 548; 95, 609; 95, 613; 2001, 21, 115; 21, 116; 89, 578) committed in the field of the use of manpower, remuneration, organisation of transport operation, regulation of working and rest time, traffic or vehicle safety and environmental protection, or if regardless of the offence committed by the person, the agency which grants the licence does not question the person's suitability to organise carriage of passengers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 n&otilde;udele peab vastama ka f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust tegevusloa taotleja v&otilde;i selle omanik sellest olenemata, kas ta on m&auml;&auml;ranud vedude eest vastutava isiku. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The applicant for a licence or the holder of a licence who is a natural person shall also comply with the requirement set out in subsection (1) of this section regardless of whether the natural person has appointed a person responsible for transport operation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Vedude eest vastutava isiku ametialane p&auml;devus </eesti>
<inglise>Professional competence of person responsible for transport operation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vedude eest vastutavat isikut peetakse p&auml;devaks, kui ta on Teede- ja Sideministeeriumi tunnustatud &otilde;ppeasutuses l&auml;binud vedude eest vastutava isiku koolituskursuse ja sooritanud kursuse kirjaliku l&otilde;pueksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person responsible for transport operation is deemed to be professionally competent if he or she has undergone a training course for persons responsible for transport operation in an educational institution recognised by the Ministry of Transport and Communications and has passed the written final exam of such course. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vedude eest vastutava isiku koolituskursust ei pea l&auml;bima isik, kes on v&auml;hemalt viis aastat olnud vedaja s&otilde;itjateveo korraldaja ja on sooritanud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud koolituskursuse kirjaliku l&otilde;pueksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person who has worked as the organiser of carriage of passengers with a carrier for at least five years and who has passed the written final exam of the training course specified in subsection (1) of this section is not required to undergo a training course for persons responsible for transport operation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Taksoveo eest vastutavat isikut peetakse p&auml;devaks, kui ta on Teede- ja Sideministeeriumi tunnustatud &otilde;ppeasutuses l&auml;binud taksovedude eest vastutava isiku koolituskursuse ja sooritanud kursuse kirjaliku l&otilde;pueksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person responsible for taxi service is deemed to be professionally competent if he or she has undergone a training course for persons responsible for taxi service in an educational institution recognised by the Ministry of Transport and Communications and has passed the written final exam of such course. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Taksoveo eest vastutava isiku koolituskursust ei pea l&auml;bima isik, kes on v&auml;hemalt viis aastat olnud vedaja s&otilde;itjateveo korraldaja ja on sooritanud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud koolituskursuse kirjaliku l&otilde;pueksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person who has worked as the organiser of carriage of passengers with a carrier for at least five years and who has passed the written final exam of the training course specified in subsection (3) of this section is not required to undergo a training course for persons responsible for taxi service. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Vedude eest vastutava isiku koolituskursust ei ole vaja l&auml;bida ega l&otilde;pueksamit sooritada isikul, kellel on k&otilde;rgkoolidiplom, mis t&otilde;endab piisavaid teadmisi koolituskursuse &otilde;ppekavas loetletud ainetes. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A person who holds a diploma issued by an institution of higher education which certifies adequate expertise in the subjects listed in the curriculum of the training course for persons responsible for transport operation is not required to undergo the training course or pass the final exam of such training course. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Teede- ja sideminister kinnitab vedude eest vastutava isiku kvalifikatsioonin&otilde;uded, koolituskursuse &otilde;ppekava, koolitustunnistuse vormi ning k&otilde;rgkoolide ja nendes ettevalmistatavate erialade loetelu, mille l&otilde;petajale antud k&otilde;rgkoolidiplom vastab k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall approve the qualification requirements for persons responsible for transport operation, curricula of training courses, format of the certificates of training and a list of the institutions of higher education and areas of specialisation provided by such institutions which grant diplomas of higher education to their graduates in compliance with the provisions of subsection (5) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa, s&otilde;idukikaardi ja liiniloa taotlemiseks esitatavad dokumendid </eesti>
<inglise>Documents submitted upon application for licence, vehicle card and line permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa taotleja esitab loa andjale j&auml;rgmised dokumendid: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The applicant for a licence shall submit the following documents to the agency which grants the licence: </inglise>
<eesti>1) avaldus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an application; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &auml;riregistrisse kantud ettev&otilde;tja puhul registrikaardi &auml;rakiri, seaduse alusel teise registrisse kantud juriidilise isiku puhul selle registri v&auml;ljav&otilde;te; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in the case of an undertaking entered in the commercial register, a transcript of the registry card, and in the case of a legal person entered in another register pursuant to an Act, an extract from such register; </inglise>
<eesti>3) asutatava &auml;ri&uuml;hingu asutamislepingu notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud &auml;rakiri; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a notarised transcript of the memorandum of association of the company to be founded; </inglise>
<eesti>4) p&otilde;hikiri v&otilde;i &uuml;hinguleping (v&auml;lja arvatud &auml;riregistrisse kantud ettev&otilde;tja puhul); </eesti>
<inglise>4) articles of association or partnership agreement (except if an undertaking is entered in the commercial register); </inglise>
<eesti>5) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud rahalist seisu iseloomustavad dokumendid; </eesti>
<inglise>5) documents describing the financial position specified in subsection 36 (2) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>6) Maksuameti kohaliku asutuse t&otilde;end maksuv&otilde;lgnevuse puudumise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a certificate from a local Tax Board office concerning the absence of tax arrears; </inglise>
<eesti>7) vedude eest vastutava isiku m&auml;&auml;ramist ja tema ametialast p&auml;devust kinnitavad dokumendid; </eesti>
<inglise>7) documents confirming the appointment of a person responsible for transport operation and his or her professional competence; </inglise>
<eesti>8) riigil&otilde;ivu tasumise kviitung (v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui loa v&auml;ljaandja on valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus). </eesti>
<inglise>8) a receipt of payment of the state fee (except if a licence is granted by a rural municipality government or city government). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahvusvahelise s&otilde;itjateveo korraldamise &otilde;iguse saamiseks esitab &uuml;histranspordiloa omanik Teede- ja Sideministeeriumile j&auml;rgmised dokumendid: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to be granted the right to engage in international carriage of passengers, the holder of a public transport licence shall submit the following documents to the Ministry of Transport and Communications: </inglise>
<eesti>1) avaldus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an application; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;histranspordiluba; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the public transport licence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) Maksuameti kohaliku asutuse t&otilde;end maksuv&otilde;lgnevuse puudumise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a certificate from a local Tax Board office concerning the absence of tax arrears; </inglise>
<eesti>4) rahvusvaheliste vedude eest vastutava isiku m&auml;&auml;ramist ja tema ametialast p&auml;devust kinnitavad dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>4) documents confirming the appointment of a person responsible for international transport operation and his or her professional competence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&otilde;idukikaardi taotleja esitab kaardi andjale j&auml;rgmised dokumendid: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The applicant for a vehicle card shall submit the following documents to the agency which grants the vehicle card: </inglise>
<eesti>1) avaldus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an application; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tegevusluba; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the licence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &auml;riregistrisse kantud ettev&otilde;tja puhul registrikaardi &auml;rakiri, seaduse alusel teise registrisse kantud juriidilise isiku puhul selle registri v&auml;ljav&otilde;te (esitatakse ainult esimese s&otilde;idukikaardi saamisel); </eesti>
<inglise>3) in the case of an undertaking entered in the commercial register, a transcript of the registry card, and in the case of a legal person entered in another register pursuant to an Act, an extract from such register (to be submitted only upon receipt of the first vehicle card); </inglise>
<eesti>4) s&otilde;iduki registreerimistunnistus; </eesti>
<inglise>4) registration certificate of a vehicle; </inglise>
<eesti>5) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud omavahendite olemasolu t&otilde;endavad dokumendid (v&auml;lja arvatud taksoveo puhul); </eesti>
<inglise>5) documents certifying the existence of the own funds specified in subsection 36 (3) of this Act (except in the case of taxi service); </inglise>
<eesti>6) rahvusvahelisele s&otilde;itjateveole lubatud s&otilde;iduki tehno&uuml;levaatuse tunnistus; </eesti>
<inglise>6) certificate of roadworthiness test issued to a vehicle permitted to engage in international carriage of passengers; </inglise>
<eesti>7) renditud s&otilde;iduki puhul rendileping; </eesti>
<inglise>7) in the case of a leased vehicle, commercial lease contract; </inglise>
<eesti>8) Maksuameti kohaliku asutuse t&otilde;end maksuv&otilde;lgnevuse puudumise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>8) a certificate from a local Tax Board office concerning the absence of tax arrears; </inglise>
<eesti>9) riigil&otilde;ivu tasumise kviitung (v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui s&otilde;idukikaardi andja on valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus). </eesti>
<inglise>9) a receipt of payment of the state fee (except if a vehicle card is granted by a rural municipality or city government). </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Liiniloa taotleja esitab loa andjale j&auml;rgmised dokumendid: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The applicant for a line permit shall submit the following documents to the agency which grants the line permit: </inglise>
<eesti>1) avaldus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an application; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;histranspordiluba; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the public transport licence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) s&otilde;iduplaani kavand; </eesti>
<inglise>3) draft timetable; </inglise>
<eesti>4) Maksuameti kohaliku asutuse t&otilde;end maksuv&otilde;lgnevuse puudumise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a certificate from a local Tax Board office concerning the absence of tax arrears; </inglise>
<eesti>5) riigil&otilde;ivu tasumise kviitung (v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui s&otilde;idukikaardi andja on valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus). </eesti>
<inglise>5) a receipt of payment of the state fee (except if a vehicle card is granted by a rural municipality or city government). </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tegevusloa, s&otilde;idukikaardi, liiniloa ja rahvusvahelise s&otilde;itjateveo korraldamise &otilde;iguse andjale esitatud dokumendid ei kuulu avaldamisele kolmandatele isikutele, kui seadusega ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The documents submitted to the agencies which grant licences, vehicle cards and line permits and the right to organise international carriage of passengers are not subject to disclosure to third persons unless otherwise provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa, s&otilde;idukikaardi ja liiniloa taotluse l&auml;bivaatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Review of applications for licences, vehicle cards and line permits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa andja annab tegevusloa v&otilde;i teatab loa taotlejale tegevusloa andmise keeldumisest kirjalikult 30 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 39 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud dokumentide esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An agency which grants licences shall grant a licence or inform the applicant for the licence in writing of the refusal to grant the licence within thirty calendar days after the submission of the documents specified in subsection 39 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teede- ja Sideministeerium teeb &uuml;histranspordiloale kande rahvusvahelise s&otilde;itjateveo korraldamise &otilde;iguse kohta v&otilde;i teatab loa taotlejale kande tegemise keeldumisest kirjalikult 30 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 39 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud dokumentide esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Ministry of Transport and Communications shall make an entry on a public transport licence concerning the right to organise international carriage of passengers or inform the applicant for the licence in writing of the refusal to make such entry within thirty calendar days after the submission of the documents specified in subsection 39 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&otilde;idukikaardi andja annab s&otilde;idukikaardi v&otilde;i teatab kaardi taotlejale s&otilde;idukikaardi andmise keeldumisest kirjalikult 15 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 39 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud dokumentide esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An agency which grants vehicle cards shall grant a vehicle card or inform the applicant for the vehicle card in writing of the refusal to grant the vehicle card within fifteen calendar days after the submission of the documents specified in subsection 39 (3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Liiniloa andja annab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 34 l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatud avaliku konkursi alusel valitud vedajale liiniloa 15 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast avaliku konkursi l&otilde;ppemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An agency which grants line permits shall grant a line permit to a carrier selected on the basis of a public competition specified in subsection 34 (5) of this Act within fifteen days after the conclusion of the public competition. </inglise>
<eesti>Teistele konkursil osalejatele teatatakse konkursi tulemustest kirjalikult 15 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast konkursi l&otilde;ppemist. </eesti>
<inglise>Other participants in the competition shall be informed in writing of the results of the competition within fifteen calendar days after the conclusion of the public competition. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Liiniloa andja annab liiniloa vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 34 l&otilde;ikele 6 ilma avaliku konkursita v&otilde;i teatab loa taotlejale liiniloa andmise keeldumisest kirjalikult 30 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 39 l&otilde;ikes 4 nimetatud dokumentide esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An agency which grants line permits shall grant a line permit without organising a public competition pursuant to subsection 34 (6) of this Act or inform the applicant in writing of the refusal to grant the line permit within thirty days after the submission of the documents specified in subsection 39 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Teede- ja Sideministeerium annab liiniloa rahvusvaheliseks liiniveoks 15 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast liiniloa saamist iga asjaomase riigi p&auml;devalt ametiasutuselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Ministry of Transport and Communications shall grant a line permit for international regular services within fifteen days after receiving line permits from the competent authorities of each relevant state. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa ja liiniloa andmisest keeldumine </eesti>
<inglise>Refusal to grant licence or line permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa andja keeldub loa andmisest, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An agency which grants licences shall refuse to grant a licence if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) loa taotleja on maksuv&otilde;lglane, kui talle on v&auml;lja kuulutatud pankrot v&otilde;i kui ettev&otilde;tja eelmise tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamise p&otilde;hjus on &otilde;igusnormide rikkumine, millest ei ole m&ouml;&ouml;dunud kahte aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the applicant for the licence owes arrears or is declared bankrupt or if the reason for the revocation of a previous licence was a violation of the provisions of law committed less than two years ago; </inglise>
<eesti>2) loa taotlejat on seoses varasema majandustegevusega &uuml;le kahe korra karistatud kriminaal- v&otilde;i halduskorras maksu-, tolli-, hinna-, tarbijakaitse-, t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja v&otilde;i m&otilde;&otilde;tevahendite kasutamise n&otilde;uete rikkumise v&otilde;i riiklikku registrisse andmete esitamise korra rikkumise v&otilde;i k&auml;esolevas seaduses etten&auml;htud tegevusloa, s&otilde;idukikaardi v&otilde;i liiniloata veo korraldamise eest ning karistuse &auml;rakandmisest ei ole m&ouml;&ouml;dunud kolme aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the applicant for the licence has been punished by way of criminal or administrative procedure on more than two occasions in connection with previous economic activities for the violation of tax, customs, price, customer protection, work and rest time requirements or requirements on the use of measuring instruments, or for the violation of the procedure for submission of data to state registers, or for the organisation of transport operation without a licence, vehicle card or line permit prescribed by this Act and less than three years have passed from the date on which the person finished the serving of the sentence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) loa taotlemiseks on esitatud tegelikkusele mittevastavaid andmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the applicant for the licence has submitted inaccurate information upon application for the licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Liiniloa andja keeldub liiniloa andmisest, kui ilmneb, et veoteenus, mille osutamiseks liiniluba taotletakse, h&auml;irib varem antud liiniloa alusel veoteenuse osutamist, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui nimetatud teenust osutab ainult &uuml;ks vedaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An agency which grants line permits shall refuse to grant a line permit if it becomes known that the transport service would interfere with the provision of transport services on the basis of a line permit granted earlier except if the services in question are carried out by a single carrier. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>Liiniloa andmisest ja avaliku teenindamise lepingu s&otilde;lmimisest teatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Informing of grant of line permit and entry into public regular services contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liiniloa andja peab loa andmisest teatama &uuml;histranspordiloa andnud ametiasutusele loa andmisest alates viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An agency which grants line permits shall inform the agency which granted a public transport licence of the grant of a line permit within five working days after the permit is granted. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Veo tellija peab avaliku teenindamise lepingu s&otilde;lmimisest teatama &uuml;histranspordiloa andnud ametiasutusele lepingu s&otilde;lmimisest alates viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A party ordering a transport operation shall inform the agency which granted a public transport licence of the entry into a public service contract within five working days after the contract is entered into. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa, s&otilde;idukikaardi ja liiniloa kehtimine </eesti>
<inglise>Validity of licence, vehicle card and line permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Bussi-, trammi- ja trollibussiveo &uuml;histranspordiluba antakse viieks aastaks, kui loa taotleja ei soovi seda l&uuml;hemaks ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public transport licence for carriage by bus, tram and trolleybus shall be granted for five years unless the applicant wishes to be granted a licence for a shorter period. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Taksoveoluba antakse esmakordselt kaheks aastaks ja j&auml;rgmistel kordadel viieks aastaks, kui loa taotleja ei soovi seda l&uuml;hemaks ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A taxi licence shall be initially granted for two years and for five years on each subsequent occasion unless the applicant wishes to be granted a taxi licence for a shorter period. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&otilde;idukikaart kehtib &uuml;ksnes tegevusloa kehtivuse ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A vehicle card shall be valid only during the period of validity of a corresponding licence. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;iduki rentimise korral ei kehti s&otilde;idukikaart kauem kui rendilepingu t&auml;htaja l&otilde;puni. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of a leased vehicle, the vehicle card shall be valid only up to the expiry of the commercial lease contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui liiniloa taotleja ei soovi bussi-, trammi- v&otilde;i trollibussiveo liiniluba l&uuml;hemaks ajaks, antakse see esmakordselt kaheks aastaks ja j&auml;rgmistel kordadel viieks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A line permit for carriage by bus, tram or trolleybus shall be initially granted for two years and for five years on each subsequent occasion unless the applicant for a line permit wishes to be granted a line permit for a shorter period. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Liiniluba kehtib &uuml;ksnes &uuml;histranspordiloa kehtivuse ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A line permit shall be valid only during the period of validity of a corresponding public transport licence. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;histranspordiloa kehtetuks tunnistamise korral v&otilde;i loa t&auml;htaja l&otilde;ppemisel liiniloa kehtivus l&otilde;peb. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of revocation of the public transport licence or expiry of the licence, the line permit shall expire. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui &uuml;histranspordiloa t&auml;htaeg l&otilde;peb liiniloa t&auml;htajast varem, peab vedaja enne &uuml;histranspordiloa t&auml;htaja l&otilde;ppemist esitama taotluse uue &uuml;histranspordiloa saamiseks k&auml;esolevas seaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>If the public transport licence expires earlier than the line permit, the carrier shall submit an application for the grant of a new public transport licence before the expiry of the public transport licence pursuant to the procedure provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa, liiniloa ja s&otilde;idukikaardi andmed </eesti>
<inglise>Data entered on licence, line permit and vehicle card </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Bussiveoks antavale &uuml;histranspordiloale m&auml;rgitakse vedaja nimi, registreeritud asukoht ja registrikood, loa andja nimetus, loa number, loa andmise kuup&auml;ev ning loa kehtimise aeg. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public transport licence granted for carriage by bus shall contain the name of the carrier, the registered location and registry code thereof, the name of the agency which grants the licence, the number, date of grant of the licence and the period of validity of the licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Taksoveoloale m&auml;rgitakse vedaja nimi, registreeritud asukoht ja registrikood, loa andja nimetus, loa number, loa andmise kuup&auml;ev, loa kehtimise aeg ning vedaja p&otilde;hiline teeninduspiirkond. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A taxi licence shall contain the name of the carrier, the registered location and registry code thereof, the name of the agency which grants the licence, the number, date of grant of the licence and the period of validity of the licence and the main territory within which the carrier provides services. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&otilde;idukikaardile m&auml;rgitakse vedaja nimi, registreeritud asukoht ja registrikood, tegevusloa number, s&otilde;iduki mark, mudel, registreerimism&auml;rk ja istekohtade arv, s&otilde;iduki omaniku nimi, s&otilde;idukikaardi andja nimetus ning kaardi andmise kuup&auml;ev ja kehtimise aeg. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A vehicle card shall contain the name of the carrier, the registered location and registry code thereof, the number of the licence, make, model, registration plate, the number of seats and the name of the owner of the vehicle, the name of the agency which grants the licence, date of grant of the licence and the priod of validity of the vehicle card. </inglise>
<eesti>Takso s&otilde;idukikaardile kantakse ka vedaja p&otilde;hiline teeninduspiirkond. </eesti>
<inglise>The main territory within which a carrier provides services shall be entered on a vehicle card of a taxi. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Trammi- ja trollibussiveoks antava &uuml;histranspordiloa ja s&otilde;idukikaardi andmete loetelu ning loa ja kaardi vormi kehtestab lube andev linnavolikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The list of data entered on a public transport licence and vehicle card granted for carriage by tram or trolleybus and the format of a licence and vehicle card shall be established by the city council which grants the licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Bussiveoks antavale liiniloale m&auml;rgitakse vedaja nimi, registreeritud asukoht ja registrikood, liini nimetus ning liini alg- ja l&otilde;pp-punkt, loa andja nimetus, loa number, loa andmise kuup&auml;ev ning loa kehtimise aeg. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) On a line permit issued for carriage by bus, the name of the carrier, the registered location and registry code thereof, the name of the line and the points of departure and destination thereof, the name of the agency which grants the licence, the number, date of grant of the licence and the period of validity of the licence shall be entered. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 nimetatud vedaja p&otilde;hiliseks teeninduspiirkonnaks on registreerimisj&auml;rgse omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse haldusterritoorium v&otilde;i selle osa. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The territory within which a carrier provides services specified in subsections (2) and (3) of this section shall be the administrative territory or a part of the administrative territory of the local government of the carrier's registration. </inglise>
<eesti>Teeninduspiirkonnaks v&otilde;ib omavalitsusorganite omavahelisel kokkuleppel olla ka teise omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse haldusterritoorium. </eesti>
<inglise>On a mutual agreement between local government bodies, the administrative territory of the other local government may also be the territory within which services are provided. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1, 2 ja 5 nimetatud lubade ning l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud s&otilde;idukikaardi vormi kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall establish the formats for the licences specified in subsections (1), (2) and (5) and of the vehicle card specified in subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>Vedaja veokohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Carrier's obligation to carry </inglise>
<eesti>Liiniloa omanik on kohustatud korraldama liiniloale m&auml;rgitud vedu. </eesti>
<inglise>The holder of a line permit has the obligation to perform the transport operation entered on the line permit. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa, s&otilde;idukikaardi ja liiniloa kehtivuse peatamine ning nende kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension and revocation of licence, vehicle card and line permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa andja v&otilde;ib loa omanikule teha puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks ettekirjutuse v&otilde;i ta v&otilde;ib tegevusloa v&otilde;i selle alusel antava s&otilde;idukikaardi kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks peatada v&otilde;i tunnistada kehtetuks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An agency which grants licences may issue a precept to the holder of a licence for elimination of deficiencies or suspend a licence or a vehicle card granted on the basis thereof for a designated period or revoke a licence or a vehicle card granted on the basis thereof if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) loa omanik ei vasta enam k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 35 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>1) the holder of the licence no longer complies with the requirements provided for in &sect; 35 of this Act, or </inglise>
<eesti>2) loa omaniku tegevuses ilmnevad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 41 nimetatud asjaolud. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the facts specified in &sect; 41 of this Act become known with regard to the operation of the holder of the licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Liiniloa andja v&otilde;ib loa omanikule teha puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks ettekirjutuse v&otilde;i ta v&otilde;ib liiniloa kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks peatada v&otilde;i tunnistada kehtetuks, kui loa omanik: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An agency which grants line permits may issue a precept to the holder of a line permit for elimination of deficiencies or suspend a line permit for a designated period or revoke a line permit if the holder of the permit: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ei t&auml;ida temale k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel vastuv&otilde;etud &otilde;igusaktiga kehtestatud n&otilde;udeid v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>1) fails to comply with the requirements established for the holder of the permit by this Act or legislation adopted on the basis thereof, or </inglise>
<eesti>2) kui ta ei ole alustanud tegevust s&otilde;iduplaaniga etten&auml;htud ajal v&otilde;i ei ole korraldanud vedu regulaarselt. </eesti>
<inglise>2) has not commenced operation at the time prescribed by the timetable or has not organised transport operations on a regular basis. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui tegevusloa andja tunnistab kehtetuks kommertsliinivedu korraldava vedaja &uuml;histranspordiloa, peab ta kehtetuks tunnistamisest alates viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul teatama sellest liiniloa andjale, kes tunnistab kehtetuks ka vedaja liiniloa. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an agency which grants licences revokes a public transport licence of a carrier which provides commercial regular services, the agency shall inform the corresponding agency which granted the line permit within five working days after the revocation and the agency which grants line permits shall also revoke the line permit granted to the carrier. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui tegevusloa andja tunnistab kehtetuks avalikku liinivedu korraldava vedaja &uuml;histranspordiloa, peab ta kehtetuks tunnistamisest alates viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul teatama sellest asutusele, kellega on vedajal s&otilde;lmitud avaliku teenindamise leping. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If an agency which grants licences revokes a public transport licence of a carrier which provides public regular services, the agency shall inform the agency with which the carrier has entered into a public services contract within five working days after the revocation. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tegevusloa andja v&otilde;ib tegevusloa tunnistada kehtetuks ka loa omaniku enda taotlusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An agency which grants licences may revoke a licence also at the request of the holder of the licence. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui tegevusloa omanikul on liiniluba, peab ta taotlusest teatama tegevusloa andjale k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 6 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htajal. </eesti>
<inglise>If the holder of a licence also holds a line permit, the holder of the licence shall notify the agency which granted the licence of such request within the term provided for in subsection (6) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Liiniloa andja v&otilde;ib liiniloa tunnistada kehtetuks ka loa omaniku enda taotlusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An agency which grants line permits may revoke a line permit also at the request of the holder of the line permit. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui vedaja taotleb liiniloa kehtetuks tunnistamist, peab ta sellest teatama loa andjale v&auml;hemalt 45 kalendrip&auml;eva ette. </eesti>
<inglise>If a carrier requests the revocation of a line permit, the carrier shall notify the agency which granted the permit at least forty-five calendar days in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kui tegevusloa, s&otilde;idukikaardi v&otilde;i liiniloa t&auml;htaeg on l&otilde;ppenud v&otilde;i kui nende kehtivus on peatatud v&otilde;i kui tegevusluba, s&otilde;idukikaart v&otilde;i liiniluba on tunnistatud kehtetuks, tuleb dokument selle andjale viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul tagastada. (8) Kui kontrolli tulemusel selgub, et vedaja ei vasta hea majandusseisundi n&otilde;udele, kuid tema tegevuse majandusn&auml;itajad t&otilde;endavad, et ta on edaspidi suuteline hea majandusseisundi n&otilde;uet t&auml;itma, v&otilde;ib tegevusloa andja tegevusloa kehtivust mitte peatada ja lubada korraldada s&otilde;itjatevedu, kuid mitte kauem kui &uuml;ks aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Upon expiry, suspension or revocation of a licence, vehicle card or line permit, such document shall be returned to the agency which granted the document within five working days. (8) If as a result of checks, it becomes evident that a carrier does not comply with the requirement of good economic standing but economic indicators characterising the carrier's operation certify that the carrier will be able to comply with the requirement of good economic standing in the future, the agency which granted the licence has the right not to suspend the licence and to allow the carrier to organise the carriage of passengers, however, for not longer than for one year. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhuveo ajutine keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Temporary prohibition of occasional services </inglise>
<eesti>Kui &uuml;histranspordiloa v&otilde;i liiniloa alusel korraldatav vedu on k&auml;esoleva seadusega vastuolus, v&otilde;ib tegevusloa andja luba kehtetuks tunnistamata keelata selle omanikul ajutiselt korraldada juhuvedu. </eesti>
<inglise>If transport operations organised on the basis of a public transport licence or line permit are in conflict with this Act, the agency which issued the licence may temporarily prohibit the holder of the licence to organise occasional services without revoking the licence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>Rahvusvaheline s&otilde;itjatevedu </eesti>
<inglise>International carriage of passengers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui seadus ei n&auml;e ette teisiti, on &otilde;igus korraldada rahvusvahelist juhuvedu ja taotleda rahvusvahelist liiniluba vedajal, kellel on k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 1 nimetatud kandega &uuml;histranspordiluba ning kes vastab Eesti Vabariigi v&auml;lislepingus s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A carrier who holds a public transport licence bearing the entry specified in clause (2) 1) of this section and who complies with the requirements provided by the international agreements entered into by the Republic of Estonia has the right to organise international occasional services and apply for an international line permit unless otherwise provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud v&auml;lislepingutest tulenevate n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmist ning piirangute rakendamist korraldab Teede- ja Sideministeerium, kes: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Compliance with the requirements arising from the international agreements specified in (1) of this section and implementation of restrictions shall be organised by the Ministry of Transport and Communications who shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teeb &uuml;histranspordiloale kande selle kohta, et vedajal on &otilde;igus korraldada k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 kohast rahvusvahelist vedu, ning m&auml;rgib loale vedaja suhtes kohaldatavad piirangud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) make an entry on a public transport licence concerning the carrier's right to perform international transport operations pursuant to subsection (1) of this section and indicate the restrictions implemented with regard to the carrier on the permit; </inglise>
<eesti>2) annab liiniloa rahvusvaheliseks liiniveoks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) grant line permits for international regular services. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Rahvusvahelise liiniloa vormi kehtestab teede- ja sideminister, l&auml;htudes Eesti Vabariigi v&auml;lislepingu s&auml;tetest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall establish the format for international line permits in adherence with the provisions of international agreements entered into by the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Rahvusvahelisele liinibussiveole v&otilde;ib lubada vedaja, kes on korraldanud s&otilde;itjate rahvusvahelist juhuvedu v&otilde;i riigisisest kaugliinibussivedu v&auml;hemalt kaks aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A carrier who has organised occasional international or domestic long-distance carriage of passengers by bus for at least two years may be permitted to engage in international regular carriage of passengers by bus. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui &uuml;histranspordiloa alusel veo korraldamine on vastuolus Eesti Vabariigi v&auml;lislepinguga, v&otilde;ib Teede- ja Sideministeerium teha loa omanikule ettekirjutuse puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks, peatada ajutiselt loale tehtud kande kehtivuse v&otilde;i tunnistada kande v&otilde;i loa kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If the organisation of transport operations on the basis of a public transport licence is in conflict with an international agreement entered into by the Republic of Estonia, the Ministry of Transport and Communications may issue a precept to the holder of the licence for elimination of the deficiencies, to temporarily suspend the validity of the entry made on the licence or to revoke the entry or the permit. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;idukikaardi ja s&otilde;iduplaani kontrollimiseks esitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Producing of vehicle card and timetable for inspection </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vedaja on kohustatud tagama, et &uuml;hiss&otilde;iduki juht esitab politseiametnikule v&otilde;i muule kontrollimis&otilde;igusega ametiisikule kontrollimiseks j&auml;rgmised dokumendid: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A carrier is required to ensure that the drivers of public transport vehicles produce the following documents to police officers or other officials with inspection rights: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kommertsliiniveol (kaasa arvatud eriotstarbeline vedu) s&otilde;idukikaardi ning kinnitatud s&otilde;iduplaani v&otilde;i selle koopia, millele on m&auml;rgitud liiniloa number ja loa kehtimise aeg ning liiniloa andja rekvisiidid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) in commercial regular services (including special transport operations) - a vehicle card and approved timetable or a copy thereof which sets out the number and validity period of the line permit and requisite information concerning the agency which granted the line permit; </inglise>
<eesti>2) avalikul liiniveol (kaasa arvatud eriotstarbeline vedu) s&otilde;idukikaardi ning kinnitatud s&otilde;iduplaani v&otilde;i selle koopia, millele on m&auml;rgitud avaliku teenindamise lepingu number, lepingu s&otilde;lmimise kuup&auml;ev ja kehtimise aeg ning lepingupoolte rekvisiidid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in public regular services (including special transport operations) - a vehicle card and an approved timetable or a copy thereof which sets out the number of the public service contract, date of entry into the contract and validity period of the contract and requisite information concerning the parties to the contract; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tellija ja vedaja s&otilde;lmitud lepingu alusel korraldataval eriotstarbelisel kommertsliiniveol s&otilde;idukikaardi ning s&otilde;iduplaani v&otilde;i selle koopia, millele on m&auml;rgitud veolepingu number, lepingu s&otilde;lmimise kuup&auml;ev ja kehtimise aeg ning lepingupoolte rekvisiidid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) in special commercial regular services provided on the basis of a contract entered into between an ordering party and a carrier - a vehicle card and a timetable or a copy thereof which sets out the number and validity period of such contract and requisite information concerning the parties to the contract; </inglise>
<eesti>4) juhu- ja taksoveol s&otilde;idukikaardi. </eesti>
<inglise>4) in occasional services and taxi service - a vehicle card. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Taksoveo paremaks korraldamiseks v&otilde;ib linna- v&otilde;i vallavolikogu kehtestada takso t&ouml;&ouml;ajagraafiku sisseseadmise n&otilde;ude. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Rural municipality and city councils may establish a requirement for establishment of working schedules for taxies. </inglise>
<eesti>Graafiku kinnitamise ja andmise korra kehtestab linna- v&otilde;i vallavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>Rural municipality and city governments shall establish the procedure for the approval and issue of the working schedules. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>Informatsiooni saamine registrist </eesti>
<inglise>Obtainment of information from register </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;itjateveo tegevuslubade ja liinilubade andmiseks ning kehtetuks tunnistamiseks on tegevusloa ja liiniloa andjatel &otilde;igus saada registritest informatsiooni andmekogude seaduses (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597; 2001, 7, 17; 17, 77) kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Agencies which grant licences or line permits have the right to obtain information from registers pursuant to the procedure established by the Databases Act (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597; 2001, 7, 17; 17, 77) for the grant or revocation of licences for the carriage of passengers and for the grant or revocation of line permits. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>Loata tegevuse peatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension of unauthorised operation </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloata, liiniloata v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 49 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-4 nimetatud dokumentideta veondustegevuse peatab politseiametnik v&otilde;i muu selleks seaduse alusel &otilde;igust omav ametiisik. </eesti>
<inglise>Transport operations performed without a licence, line permit or document specified in clauses 49 (1) 1) -4) of this Act shall be suspended by police officers or other officials who have the right to suspend such operations pursuant to law. </inglise>
<eesti>9. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 9 </inglise>
<eesti>Veo &uuml;ldeeskiri </eesti>
<inglise>General Rules for Transport Operations </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 52. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 52. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;itjate bussiliiniveo, bussijuhuveo, taksoveo ja pagasiveo &uuml;ldeeskiri </eesti>
<inglise>General rules for regular carriage of passengers by bus, occasional carriage of passengers by bus, taxi service and carriage of baggage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&otilde;itjate bussiliiniveo, bussijuhuveo, taksoveo ja pagasiveo &uuml;ldeeskirja kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The general rules for regular carriage of passengers by bus, occasional carriage of passengers by bus, taxi service and carriage of baggage shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud &uuml;ldeeskirja alusel kehtestada kohaliku bussiliiniveo, trammi- ja trollibussiliiniveo, taksoveo ja pagasiveo eeskirja, mis ei ole vastuolus nimetatud &uuml;ldeeskirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) On the basis of the general rules specified in subsection (1) of this section, rural municipality and city councils may establish rules for local regular services by bus, tram or trolleybus, for taxi service and for carriage of baggage, which must not be in conflict with the general rules. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudtee-, vee- ja lennuliikluses kehtestatakse s&otilde;itjateveo ning pagasiveo &uuml;ldeeskiri teiste seaduste alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) General rules for the carriage of passengers and baggage in railway, waterway and air traffic shall be established on the basis of other Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 53. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 53. </inglise>
<eesti>Kergete kaubasaadetiste vedu ja veoeeskiri </eesti>
<inglise>Carriage of lightweight consignments and rules for carriage thereof </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Bussis v&otilde;i maanteeliikluses kasutatavas muus &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukis v&otilde;ib samal ajal s&otilde;itjate ja nende pagasiga vedada ka kergeid kaubasaadetisi tingimusel, et see on s&otilde;idukis viibijaile ohutu ega takista t&auml;ita tegevusloaga etten&auml;htud kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Lightweight consignments may be carried by bus or other public transport vehicle used in road traffic at the same time with passengers and their baggage on condition that such carriage is safe for the persons staying in the vehicle and it does not prevent the performance of the obligations prescribed by the licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukites kergete kaubasaadetiste veoeeskirja kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall establish the rules for carriage of lightweight consignments by public transport vehicles specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudtee-, vee- ja lennuliikluses kehtestatakse kergete kaubasaadetiste veoeeskiri teiste seaduste alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The rules for carriage of lightweight consignments in railway, waterway and air traffic shall be established on the basis of other Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>10. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
